{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GJSHneUfPq2HDVGFFubZ8D","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Market Structure Calendar — 2026\n2\t\n3\t*Last updated: 2026-02-22*\n4\t*Disclaimer: Educational research — not investment advice.*\n5\t\n6\tThis calendar tracks recurring structural market events that create tradeable edges. These are events no API provides — they come from our own strategy research. Both the Morning Brief and Eagle Eye pipelines read this file automatically.\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## Triple Witching + S&P Rebalancing\n11\t\n12\tTriple Witch (stock index futures, index options, and single stock options expire simultaneously) occurs on the 3rd Friday of Mar/Jun/Sep/Dec — the same day as S&P 500 quarterly rebalancing. Combined, these events move $5-6.5T in notional value.\n13\t\n14\t**Strategy**: Long Monday open of witching week → exit Thursday close. Avoid witching Friday (14% win rate since 2021). Avoid the witching hour (3-4 PM, 31% win rate). Expect weakness in the following week.\n15\t\n16\t| Expiration Date | T-9 (Positioning Starts) | T-3 to T-1 (Strongest Edge) | Week After (Bearish) |\n17\t|-----------------|--------------------------|------------------------------|----------------------|\n18\t| **Mar 20** | Mar 9 (Mon) | Mar 17-19 (Tue-Thu) | Mar 23-27 |\n19\t| **Jun 19** | Jun 8 (Mon) | Jun 16-18 (Tue-Thu) | Jun 22-26 |\n20\t| **Sep 18** | Sep 7 (Mon) | Sep 15-17 (Tue-Thu) | Sep 21-25 |\n21\t| **Dec 18** | Dec 7 (Mon) | Dec 15-17 (Tue-Thu) | Dec 21-24 |\n22\t\n23\t**Key stats**: Pre-expiration rally averages +0.82% (T-9 to T-1). T-3 to T-1 averages +0.47% (134.59% annualized). Sep post-witch week is historically the worst.\n24\t\n25\t**Full research**: `Strategies/TripleWitch.md`\n26\t\n27\t---\n28\t\n29\t## FOMC Meetings\n30\t\n31\t8 scheduled meetings. Rate decision announced Day 2 at 2:00 PM ET. SEP meetings include dot plot and economic projections.\n32\t\n33\t| Meeting Dates | Decision Day | Type | Notes |\n34\t|---------------|-------------|------|-------|\n35\t| Jan 27-28 | Jan 28 | Regular | **DONE** — Held at 3.50-3.75% (10-2 vote) |\n36\t| **Mar 17-18** | Mar 18 | **SEP** | First 2026 dot plot. CME: 60% hold / 38% cut |\n37\t| Apr 28-29 | Apr 29 | Regular | |\n38\t| **Jun 16-17** | Jun 17 | **SEP** | Coincides with Triple Witch week |\n39\t| Jul 28-29 | Jul 29 | Regular | |\n40\t| **Sep 15-16** | Sep 16 | **SEP** | Coincides with Triple Witch week |\n41\t| Oct 27-28 | Oct 28 | Regular | |\n42\t| **Dec 8-9** | Dec 9 | **SEP** | 10 days before Triple Witch |\n43\t\n44\t**Current pricing**: 3 rate cuts (75 bps) priced by year-end. Fed Funds at 3.50-3.75%.\n45\t\n46\t---\n47\t\n48\t## AAPL Buyback Blackout Windows\n49\t\n50\tCorporate buyback blackout begins 35 calendar days before earnings and lifts after the report. During blackout, the corporate bid is removed — creating structural weakness early/mid phase and recovery late phase.\n51\t\n52\t**Strategy**: Verified +12.13% return on Jan 2026 AAPL cycle. See `Strategies/Buyback-Blackout-Earnings-Flow-Strategy.md`.\n53\t\n54\t| Quarter | Expected Earnings | Blackout Start (~35 days prior) | Seasonality |\n55\t|---------|-------------------|--------------------------------|-------------|\n56\t| Q2 FY26 | ~Apr 30 | ~Mar 26 | Weak (April seasonality) |\n57\t| Q3 FY26 | ~Jul 30 | ~Jun 25 | **Strongest** (+3.46% historical) |\n58\t| Q4 FY26 | ~Oct 29 | ~Sep 24 | Moderate |\n59\t| Q1 FY27 | ~Jan 28 | ~Dec 24 | Moderate-Strong |\n60\t\n61\t*Earnings dates are estimates based on AAPL's historical pattern. Confirm via earnings calendar closer to each date.*\n62\t\n63\t---\n64\t\n65\t## Russell Reconstitution\n66\t\n67\t**NEW in 2026**: Russell US indices move to semi-annual reconstitution (was annual).\n68\t\n69\t| Event | Date | Impact |\n70\t|-------|------|--------|\n71\t| Annual reconstitution (June) | **Jun 26** (4th Friday) | Full membership review. Historically generates ~$100B in rebalancing flows. |\n72\t| Semi-annual reconstitution (December) | **Dec 11** (2nd Friday) | New additions and membership changes. First-ever December reconstitution. Changes reflected at open Mon Dec 14. |\n73\t\n74\t**Full research**: `Cycles/Index-Rebalancing-Calendar-Trading.md`\n75\t\n76\t---\n77\t\n78\t## Monthly Options Expiration (OpEx)\n79\t\n80\t3rd Friday of each month. Quarterly dates (bolded) coincide with Triple Witch.\n81\t\n82\t| Month | OpEx Date | Notes |\n83\t|-------|-----------|-------|\n84\t| January | 16 | |\n85\t| February | 20 | |\n86\t| **March** | **20** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance** |\n87\t| April | 17 | |\n88\t| May | 15 | |\n89\t| **June** | **19** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance + FOMC week** |\n90\t| July | 17 | |\n91\t| August | 21 | |\n92\t| **September** | **18** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance + FOMC week** |\n93\t| October | 16 | |\n94\t| November | 20 | |\n95\t| **December** | **18** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance** |\n96\t\n97\t---\n98\t\n99\t## Seasonal Edges\n100\t\n101\tStatistical patterns from historical data. Use as context, not standalone signals.\n102\t\n103\t| Window | Dates (2026) | Historical Edge | Notes |\n104\t|--------|-------------|-----------------|-------|\n105\t| January Effect | Jan 1-31 | Small-caps outperform large-caps | Tax-loss selling recovery |\n106\t| Turn-of-Month | Last trading day + first 3 of new month | +0.14% avg vs -0.04% rest of month | Payroll/pension fund flows |\n107\t| Sell in May | May 1 - Oct 31 | Weaker 6-month period historically | \"Sell in May and go away\" |\n108\t| September Weakness | Sep 1-30 | Worst calendar month historically | -0.5% avg return |\n109\t| Q4 Rally | Nov-Dec | Strongest 2-month period | Tax-loss selling ends, window dressing |\n110\t| Santa Claus Rally | Dec 24 - Jan 2 | +1.3% avg (since 1950) | Low volume, bullish sentiment |\n111\t\n112\t---\n113\t\n114\t## Presidential Cycle\n115\t\n116\t2026 = Year 2 of presidential term (midterm year).\n117\t\n118\t| Cycle Year | Historical Avg Return | Win Rate | 2026 Status |\n119\t|------------|----------------------|----------|-------------|\n120\t| Year 1 (post-election) | +7.0% | 60% | 2025 |\n121\t| **Year 2 (midterm)** | **+4.0%** | **55%** | **2026 ← Current** |\n122\t| Year 3 (pre-election) | +17.2% | 90% | 2027 |\n123\t| Year 4 (election) | +7.5% | 65% | 2028 |\n124\t\n125\tMidterm years tend to front-load weakness (H1) with a strong rally from the midterm low (typically Oct-Nov) into Year 3.\n126\t\n127\t**Full research**: `Cycles/Presidential Election Year Market Cycles.docx`, `Ideas/trump-media-etf-presidential-cycle-thesis.md`\n128\t\n129\t---\n130\t\n131\t## Key Convergence Dates\n132\t\n133\tDates where multiple structural events overlap — highest impact potential.\n134\t\n135\t| Date | Events Converging |\n136\t|------|-------------------|\n137\t| **Mar 17-20** | FOMC (Mar 18) + Triple Witch (Mar 20) + S&P Rebalance (Mar 20) |\n138\t| **Jun 16-26** | FOMC (Jun 17) + Triple Witch (Jun 19) + S&P Rebalance (Jun 19) + Russell Reconstitution (Jun 26) |\n139\t| **Sep 15-18** | FOMC (Sep 16) + Triple Witch (Sep 18) + S&P Rebalance (Sep 18) |\n140\t| **Dec 8-18** | FOMC (Dec 9) + Russell Semi-Annual (Dec 11) + Triple Witch (Dec 18) + S&P Rebalance (Dec 18) |\n141\t\n142\t---\n143\t\n144\t*Update this calendar annually (December) or when new dates are confirmed. AAPL earnings dates should be verified each quarter. FOMC dates are tentative until confirmed at the preceding meeting.*\n145\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"7dae4d44-1cff-4915-bf7b-e523783e1d5f","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:05.447Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
