{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GN737Y5qSdVR7TnYRjPsre","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Market Structure Calendar — 2026\n2\t\n3\t*Last updated: 2026-02-22*\n4\t*Disclaimer: Educational research — not investment advice.*\n5\t\n6\tThis calendar tracks recurring structural market events that create tradeable edges. These are events no API provides — they come from our own strategy research. Both the Morning Brief and Eagle Eye pipelines read this file automatically.\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## Triple Witching + S&P Rebalancing\n11\t\n12\tTriple Witch (stock index futures, index options, and single stock options expire simultaneously) occurs on the 3rd Friday of Mar/Jun/Sep/Dec — the same day as S&P 500 quarterly rebalancing. Combined, these events move $5-6.5T in notional value.\n13\t\n14\t**Strategy**: Long Monday open of witching week → exit Thursday close. Avoid witching Friday (14% win rate since 2021). Avoid the witching hour (3-4 PM, 31% win rate). Expect weakness in the following week.\n15\t\n16\t| Expiration Date | T-9 (Positioning Starts) | T-3 to T-1 (Strongest Edge) | Week After (Bearish) |\n17\t|-----------------|--------------------------|------------------------------|----------------------|\n18\t| **Mar 20** | Mar 9 (Mon) | Mar 17-19 (Tue-Thu) | Mar 23-27 |\n19\t| **Jun 19** | Jun 8 (Mon) | Jun 16-18 (Tue-Thu) | Jun 22-26 |\n20\t| **Sep 18** | Sep 7 (Mon) | Sep 15-17 (Tue-Thu) | Sep 21-25 |\n21\t| **Dec 18** | Dec 7 (Mon) | Dec 15-17 (Tue-Thu) | Dec 21-24 |\n22\t\n23\t**Key stats**: Pre-expiration rally averages +0.82% (T-9 to T-1). T-3 to T-1 averages +0.47% (134.59% annualized). Sep post-witch week is historically the worst.\n24\t\n25\t**Full research**: `Strategies/TripleWitch.md`\n26\t\n27\t---\n28\t\n29\t## FOMC Meetings\n30\t\n31\t8 scheduled meetings. Rate decision announced Day 2 at 2:00 PM ET. SEP meetings include dot plot and economic projections.\n32\t\n33\t| Meeting Dates | Decision Day | Type | Notes |\n34\t|---------------|-------------|------|-------|\n35\t| Jan 27-28 | Jan 28 | Regular | **DONE** — Held at 3.50-3.75% (10-2 vote) |\n36\t| **Mar 17-18** | Mar 18 | **SEP** | First 2026 dot plot. CME: 60% hold / 38% cut |\n37\t| Apr 28-29 | Apr 29 | Regular | |\n38\t| **Jun 16-17** | Jun 17 | **SEP** | Coincides with Triple Witch week |\n39\t| Jul 28-29 | Jul 29 | Regular | |\n40\t| **Sep 15-16** | Sep 16 | **SEP** | Coincides with Triple Witch week |\n41\t| Oct 27-28 | Oct 28 | Regular | |\n42\t| **Dec 8-9** | Dec 9 | **SEP** | 10 days before Triple Witch |\n43\t\n44\t**Current pricing**: 3 rate cuts (75 bps) priced by year-end. Fed Funds at 3.50-3.75%.\n45\t\n46\t---\n47\t\n48\t## AAPL Buyback Blackout Windows\n49\t\n50\tCorporate buyback blackout begins 35 calendar days before earnings and lifts after the report. During blackout, the corporate bid is removed — creating structural weakness early/mid phase and recovery late phase.\n51\t\n52\t**Strategy**: Verified +12.13% return on Jan 2026 AAPL cycle. See `Strategies/Buyback-Blackout-Earnings-Flow-Strategy.md`.\n53\t\n54\t| Quarter | Expected Earnings | Blackout Start (~35 days prior) | Seasonality |\n55\t|---------|-------------------|--------------------------------|-------------|\n56\t| Q2 FY26 | ~Apr 30 | ~Mar 26 | Weak (April seasonality) |\n57\t| Q3 FY26 | ~Jul 30 | ~Jun 25 | **Strongest** (+3.46% historical) |\n58\t| Q4 FY26 | ~Oct 29 | ~Sep 24 | Moderate |\n59\t| Q1 FY27 | ~Jan 28 | ~Dec 24 | Moderate-Strong |\n60\t\n61\t*Earnings dates are estimates based on AAPL's historical pattern. Confirm via earnings calendar closer to each date.*\n62\t\n63\t---\n64\t\n65\t## Russell Reconstitution\n66\t\n67\t**NEW in 2026**: Russell US indices move to semi-annual reconstitution (was annual).\n68\t\n69\t| Event | Date | Impact |\n70\t|-------|------|--------|\n71\t| Annual reconstitution (June) | **Jun 26** (4th Friday) | Full membership review. Historically generates ~$100B in rebalancing flows. |\n72\t| Semi-annual reconstitution (December) | **Dec 11** (2nd Friday) | New additions and membership changes. First-ever December reconstitution. Changes reflected at open Mon Dec 14. |\n73\t\n74\t**Full research**: `Cycles/Index-Rebalancing-Calendar-Trading.md`\n75\t\n76\t---\n77\t\n78\t## Monthly Options Expiration (OpEx)\n79\t\n80\t3rd Friday of each month. Quarterly dates (bolded) coincide with Triple Witch.\n81\t\n82\t| Month | OpEx Date | Notes |\n83\t|-------|-----------|-------|\n84\t| January | 16 | |\n85\t| February | 20 | |\n86\t| **March** | **20** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance** |\n87\t| April | 17 | |\n88\t| May | 15 | |\n89\t| **June** | **19** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance + FOMC week** |\n90\t| July | 17 | |\n91\t| August | 21 | |\n92\t| **September** | **18** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance + FOMC week** |\n93\t| October | 16 | |\n94\t| November | 20 | |\n95\t| **December** | **18** | **Triple Witch + S&P Rebalance** |\n96\t\n97\t---\n98\t\n99\t## Seasonal Edges\n100\t\n101\tStatistical patterns from historical data. Use as context, not standalone signals.\n102\t\n103\t| Window | Dates (2026) | Historical Edge | Notes |\n104\t|--------|-------------|-----------------|-------|\n105\t| January Effect | Jan 1-31 | Small-caps outperform large-caps | Tax-loss selling recovery |\n106\t| Turn-of-Month | Last trading day + first 3 of new month | +0.14% avg vs -0.04% rest of month | Payroll/pension fund flows |\n107\t| Sell in May | May 1 - Oct 31 | Weaker 6-month period historically | \"Sell in May and go away\" |\n108\t| September Weakness | Sep 1-30 | Worst calendar month historically | -0.5% avg return |\n109\t| Q4 Rally | Nov-Dec | Strongest 2-month period | Tax-loss selling ends, window dressing |\n110\t| Santa Claus Rally | Dec 24 - Jan 2 | +1.3% avg (since 1950) | Low volume, bullish sentiment |\n111\t\n112\t---\n113\t\n114\t## Presidential Cycle\n115\t\n116\t2026 = Year 2 of presidential term (midterm year).\n117\t\n118\t| Cycle Year | Historical Avg Return | Win Rate | 2026 Status |\n119\t|------------|----------------------|----------|-------------|\n120\t| Year 1 (post-election) | +7.0% | 60% | 2025 |\n121\t| **Year 2 (midterm)** | **+4.0%** | **55%** | **2026 ← Current** |\n122\t| Year 3 (pre-election) | +17.2% | 90% | 2027 |\n123\t| Year 4 (election) | +7.5% | 65% | 2028 |\n124\t\n125\tMidterm years tend to front-load weakness (H1) with a strong rally from the midterm low (typically Oct-Nov) into Year 3.\n126\t\n127\t**Full research**: `Cycles/Presidential Election Year Market Cycles.docx`, `Ideas/trump-media-etf-presidential-cycle-thesis.md`\n128\t\n129\t---\n130\t\n131\t## Key Convergence Dates\n132\t\n133\tDates where multiple structural events overlap — highest impact potential.\n134\t\n135\t| Date | Events Converging |\n136\t|------|-------------------|\n137\t| **Mar 17-20** | FOMC (Mar 18) + Triple Witch (Mar 20) + S&P Rebalance (Mar 20) |\n138\t| **Jun 16-26** | FOMC (Jun 17) + Triple Witch (Jun 19) + S&P Rebalance (Jun 19) + Russell Reconstitution (Jun 26) |\n139\t| **Sep 15-18** | FOMC (Sep 16) + Triple Witch (Sep 18) + S&P Rebalance (Sep 18) |\n140\t| **Dec 8-18** | FOMC (Dec 9) + Russell Semi-Annual (Dec 11) + Triple Witch (Dec 18) + S&P Rebalance (Dec 18) |\n141\t\n142\t---\n143\t\n144\t*Update this calendar annually (December) or when new dates are confirmed. AAPL earnings dates should be verified each quarter. FOMC dates are tentative until confirmed at the preceding meeting.*\n145\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"bc1f4362-f03a-446e-bc03-f6ba6ed4774c","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:21.413Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MNgeM27tnFyQVRvtKDc5ya","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"S&P 500 Nasdaq Dow weekly close May 29 2026 stock market recap\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"United States Stock Market Index - Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News | Trading Economics\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/united-states/stock-market\"},{\"title\":\"Stock Market Today (May 29, 2026): S&P 500 good for ninth consecutive week of gains after Memorial Day holiday reprieve - TheStreet\",\"url\":\"https://www.thestreet.com/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-dow-jones-sp-500-nasdaq-updates-may-29-2026\"},{\"title\":\"S&P 500 (^GSPC) Historical Data - Yahoo Finance\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EGSPC/history/\"},{\"title\":\"Stock market today: Dow, S&P 500, Nasdaq cap winning month with fresh records in AI-fueled rally as Trump nears Iran decision\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/live/dow-nasdaq-sp-gain-stock-market-today-friday-may-29-222720284.html\"},{\"title\":\"S&P 500 (SP500) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/SP500\"},{\"title\":\"S&P 500 (^GSPC) Charts, Data & News - Yahoo Finance\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EGSPC/\"},{\"title\":\"S&P 500 and Nasdaq close at new records, lifted by tech rally: Live updates\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/27/stock-market-today-live-updates.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a summary of the stock market recap for May 29, 2026:\n\n## Weekly Market Close - May 29, 2026\n\n**Major Index Performance:**\n\nThe Dow (+0.72%) dominated in the session, adding over 360 points and closing above 51,000 for the first time ever. The S&P 500 (+0.22%) notched its ninth straight week of gains and its seventh straight winning day, closing out at 7,580.08. The Nasdaq (+0.26%) also rose to 26,972, capping off an 8% increase in the month of May.\n\n**Weekly Performance:**\n\nIt's the longest such winning streak since 2023. The Russell 2000 (-0.60%) declined from record highs, sitting just below the 3K mark. It finished out at 2,919.\n\n**Notable Drivers:**\n\nThe broader rally has been supported not only by easing oil prices but also by blowout earnings and enthusiasm around the AI trade. Technology has been the best-performing sector since the March 30 market lows. In notable moves, Dell Technologies and Snowflake capped out a banner week after their respective earnings, rising by over 40% respectively during the abbreviated week.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"3de255d8-ce79-4195-ba08-dbfe3734abd9","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:21.812Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016kvYZPxhSc1bk9zWNw5USt","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"stock market news May 30 31 2026 weekend developments futures\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Stock market news for May 29, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/28/stock-market-today-live-updates.html\"},{\"title\":\"Stock futures are flat in overnight trading as June trading begins near record highs: Live updates\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/31/stock-market-today-live-updates.html\"},{\"title\":\"Stock market next week: Outlook for May 25-29, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/22/stock-market-next-week-outlook-for-may-25-29-2026.html\"},{\"title\":\"United States Stock Market Index - Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News | Trading Economics\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/united-states/stock-market\"},{\"title\":\"Schwab Market Update | Charles Schwab\",\"url\":\"https://www.schwab.com/learn/story/stock-market-update-open\"},{\"title\":\"Dow Jones Futures Live - Investing.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.investing.com/indices/us-30-futures\"},{\"title\":\"Stock Market Today (May 29, 2026): S&P 500 good for ninth consecutive week of gains after Memorial Day holiday reprieve - TheStreet\",\"url\":\"https://www.thestreet.com/stock-market-today/stock-market-today-dow-jones-sp-500-nasdaq-updates-may-29-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Pre-market Stock Trading | CNN\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnn.com/markets/premarkets\"}]\n\nBased on the latest stock market news for May 30-31, 2026:\n\n## Weekend Futures Trading (Sunday, May 31)\n\nStock futures were little changed in overnight trading Sunday as Wall Street looked to kick off June at record highs, with Dow futures inching down 30 points and S&P 500 and Nasdaq 100 futures both flat.\n\n## May Market Performance\n\nStocks wrapped up a strong May, with all three major indexes posting solid gains, with the tech-heavy Nasdaq Composite leading the advance up more than 8% for the month, the S&P 500 gaining about 5%, and the Dow Jones Industrial Average adding nearly 3%.\n\n## Friday's Strong Close (May 29)\n\nU.S. equities closed at record highs on Friday, while crude prices slipped, with the Nasdaq Composite settling up 0.2% at 26,972.62, the S&P 500 climbing 0.22% to 7,580.06, and the Dow Jones Industrial Average finishing up 363.49 points, or 0.72%, at 51,032.46.\n\n## Key Drivers\n\nNotable positive catalysts included Dell Technologies surging nearly 33%, seeing its best day on record, after the laptop maker reported a first-quarter beat on both the top and bottom lines and raised its full-year guidance. Additionally, the major averages closed at fresh highs Friday after the U.S. and Iran reached a 60-day memorandum of understanding to extend the ceasefire.\n\n## Week Ahead\n\nInvestors this week will turn their attention to Friday's closely watched nonfarm payrolls report for fresh insight into the health of the labor market and the outlook for Federal Reserve policy.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"9a7a43e0-73b4-472d-b08e-72ec93121b3c","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:23.033Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
