{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MyfpB6kK1NqxLNmJ1BzbTc","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Treasury yields weekly recap week ending May 29 2026 10-year 2-year 30-year\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"10-Year Treasury Constant Maturity Minus 2-Year Treasury Constant Maturity (T10Y2Y) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/T10Y2Y\"},{\"title\":\"Treasury Yields Snapshot: May 29, 2026 - dshort - Advisor Perspectives\",\"url\":\"https://www.advisorperspectives.com/dshort/updates/2026/05/29/treasury-yields-snapshot-may-29-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Market Yield on U.S. Treasury Securities at 30-Year Constant Maturity, Quoted on an Investment Basis (DGS30) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/DGS30\"},{\"title\":\"U.S. Treasury Yield Curve\",\"url\":\"https://streetstats.finance/rates/treasuries\"},{\"title\":\"Market Yield on U.S. Treasury Securities at 10-Year Constant Maturity, Quoted on an Investment Basis (DGS10) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/DGS10\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - H.15 - Selected Interest Rates (Daily) - May 29, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/releases/h15/\"},{\"title\":\"United States Rates & Bonds - Bloomberg - Bloomberg Markets\",\"url\":\"https://www.bloomberg.com/markets/rates-bonds/government-bonds/us\"},{\"title\":\"US Treasury Yield Curve (updated daily) - Public.com\",\"url\":\"https://public.com/treasury-yield-curve\"},{\"title\":\"Fixed income weekly commentary | Nuveen\",\"url\":\"https://www.nuveen.com/en-us/insights/fixed-income/fixed-income-weekly-commentary\"},{\"title\":\"US 10 Year Treasury Note Yield - Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/united-states/government-bond-yield\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results for Treasury yields for the week ending May 29, 2026, here are the key yields:\n\n**Treasury Yields as of May 29, 2026:**\n\n- 10-year: 4.45%\n- 2-year: 3.98%\n- 30-year: 4.98% (as of May 28)\n\n**Weekly Changes:**\n\nFor the week, the 2-year Treasury yield rose 19 basis points to 4.07%, the 10-year rose 24 basis points to 4.59% and the 30-year rose 18 basis points to 5.12%.\n\n**Key Driver:**\n\nGlobal bond markets sold off sharply this week as hotter-than-expected April CPI — headline at +0.6% month-over-month and 3.8% year-over-year — combined with surging oil prices to rattle rate expectations. However, the yield on the 10-year US Treasury note eased to around 4.44% on Friday, touching its lowest level in more than two weeks as reports of a tentative peace agreement between the US and Iran helped ease concerns over inflation and interest rates.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"a8bfcec6-813d-4a8b-bdbe-d277038b0d2f","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:32.804Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
