{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Eavnm7NuAbZUvFzf6v2A97","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"gold silver price weekly May 29 2026 close\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Current price of silver as of Friday, May 29, 2026 | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/article/current-price-of-silver-5-29-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Silver Price History - USAGOLD\",\"url\":\"https://www.usagold.com/daily-silver-price-history/\"},{\"title\":\"Gold - Price - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/commodity/gold\"},{\"title\":\"Daily Oil, Gold, Silver Technical Analysis | May 29, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://fxdailyreport.com/daily-oil-gold-silver-technical-analysis-may-29-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Silver - Price - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/commodity/silver\"},{\"title\":\"Current price of gold: May 29, 2026 | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/article/current-price-of-gold-05-29-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Live Gold Prices | Gold News And Analysis | Mining News | KITCO\",\"url\":\"https://www.kitco.com/\"},{\"title\":\"COT Silver Report - May 29, 2026 | SilverSeek\",\"url\":\"https://silverseek.com/article/cot-silver-report-may-29-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Current price of silver as of Thursday, May 28, 2026 | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/article/current-price-of-silver-5-28-2026/\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results for gold and silver prices as of May 29, 2026:\n\n## Gold Price (May 29, 2026)\n\nGold rose to 4,541.41 USD/t.oz on May 29, 2026, up 1.02% from the previous day. Another source reports that gold spot price was trading at $4,543.25 per ounce, up $40.01 (+0.89%) on the day.\n\n## Silver Price (May 29, 2026)\n\nSilver spot price was trading at $76.43 per ounce, up $0.39 (+0.51%) on the day. Additionally, silver rose to $76 an ounce on Friday and was on track for an over 3% monthly gain.\n\n## Market Context\n\nToday's gold silver price update May 29, 2026 marks the sharpest single-session recovery since early May, with both gold spot price today and silver spot price today rebounding decisively from Thursday's multi-week lows. The recovery was driven by April PCE inflation data landing broadly in line with expectations — cooling fears of an accelerated Federal Reserve tightening cycle and drawing physical buyers back into the market.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"5b6f2461-8f7e-4dca-a45c-feaaecc81cf9","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:44.852Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Commodities & forex research"}
