{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0164TXkvwRditXTjmaWRvbJ1","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"WTI Brent crude oil price weekly recap week ending May 29 2026 OPEC+\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Brent crude oil - Price - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/commodity/brent-crude-oil\"},{\"title\":\"Crude Oil - Price - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/commodity/crude-oil\"},{\"title\":\"Current price of oil as of May 29, 2026 | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/article/price-of-oil-05-29-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Brent Crude Oil Last Day Financ (BZ=F) Stock Historical Prices & Data - Yahoo Finance\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/BZ=F/history/\"},{\"title\":\"Oil Price Charts | Oilprice.com\",\"url\":\"https://oilprice.com/oil-price-charts/\"},{\"title\":\"Energy - Bloomberg - Bloomberg Markets\",\"url\":\"https://www.bloomberg.com/energy\"},{\"title\":\"Oil (USCrude) Price Forecast and Analysis for Today, Tomorrow, Next Week, and 30 Days | LiteFinance\",\"url\":\"https://www.litefinance.org/blog/analysts-opinions/oil-price-prediction-forecast/daily-and-weekly/\"},{\"title\":\"Spot Prices for Crude Oil and Petroleum Products\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/dnav/pet/pet_pri_spt_s1_d.htm\"},{\"title\":\"May 2026 Short-Term Energy Outlook\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/outlooks/steo/pdf/steo_full.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Short-Term Energy Outlook - U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA)\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/outlooks/steo/\"}]\n\n## Weekly Oil Price Recap - Week Ending May 29, 2026\n\nBased on the search results, here's a summary of crude oil prices for the week ending May 29, 2026:\n\n### Price Performance\n\nBrent crude oil futures fell about 2% to $91.2 per barrel on Friday, putting them on track for a 17% decline in May, the most since 2020. Meanwhile, WTI crude oil futures fell 1.1% to below $88 per barrel on Friday, ending May down 16.2%.\n\n### Key Driver: US-Iran Negotiations\n\nThe primary factor driving oil prices lower during the week was geopolitical developments. Reports indicated that the US and Iran reached a preliminary agreement to extend a ceasefire and ease restrictions on shipping through the Strait of Hormuz, although President Donald Trump has not yet approved the deal and Iranian state media said it has not been finalized.\n\nThe potential agreement raised expectations of an eventual end to the US-Israeli war in Iran and a reopening of the Strait of Hormuz, a critical route for about one-fifth of global oil and LNG flows. However, analysts cautioned that recovery would be gradual, with mines needing clearing, damaged infrastructure repaired and shut-in production restarted, with tanker delays also limiting supply restoration.\n\n### OPEC+ Context\n\nAdditionally, the UAE announced its departure from OPEC, effective May 1, 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"6d63d0dc-3f1f-4f75-babb-d3a72a9849da","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:46.229Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Commodities & forex research"}
