{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016G7v6zsmegK6g6dbi8mu2M","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"investment grade high yield credit spreads OAS late May 2026 weekly\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"ICE BofA US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLH0A0HYM2) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLH0A0HYM2\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA BB US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLH0A1HYBB) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLH0A1HYBB\"},{\"title\":\"Credit Spreads Explained: OAS, IG vs HY & NNN Cap Rates\",\"url\":\"https://investmentgrade.com/credit-spreads/\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA Single-B US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLH0A2HYB) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLH0A2HYB\"},{\"title\":\"US High Yield Master II Option-Adjusted Spread (Market Dail…\",\"url\":\"https://ycharts.com/indicators/us_high_yield_master_ii_optionadjusted_spread\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA CCC & Lower US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLH0A3HYC) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLH0A3HYC\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA BBB US Corporate Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLC0A4CBBB) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLC0A4CBBB\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/graph/?g=OUJ\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA US Corporate Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLC0A0CM) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLC0A0CM\"},{\"title\":\"US High Yield CCC or Below Option-Adjusted Spread (Market D…\",\"url\":\"https://ycharts.com/indicators/us_high_yield_ccc_or_below_optionadjusted_spread\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding investment-grade and high-yield credit spreads (OAS) in late May 2026:\n\n## Investment-Grade Spreads\n\nAs of early 2026, investment-grade corporate OAS is about 80 basis points, with BBB spreads roughly at 100 basis points and AA spreads roughly at 50 basis points.\n\n## High-Yield Spreads\n\nHigh yield spreads are roughly 285 basis points as of early 2026.\n\n## Market Context\n\nInvestment-grade spreads remain historically tight as of early 2026, though the data indicates these spreads have benefited from strong market confidence.\n\n## Data Sources Available\n\nThe search results point to comprehensive OAS data from the Federal Reserve's FRED database (Federal Reserve Economic Data) and ICE BofA indices, which track daily observations through late May 2026 for both investment-grade corporate bonds and various segments of high-yield bonds (including BB, single-B, and CCC-rated bonds). These sources provide detailed tracking of credit spreads across different rating categories.\n\nFor the most current late May 2026 weekly data, you can access the FRED database directly, which contains daily observations through May 28, 2026, allowing you to calculate weekly averages.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"e2a3949b-0cce-46df-b1b7-f8de0d492c75","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:48.115Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
