{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L76zB3y36i5AMWAoA2x3yo","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"US Iran 60-day ceasefire memorandum understanding May 2026 oil prices\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Oil prices turn lower as U.S.-Iran ceasefire extension awaits Trump approval\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/28/oil-prices-us-strikes-in-iran-revive-strait-of-hormuz-turmoil-fears.html\"},{\"title\":\"Oil drops 20% from 2026 peak on optimism over U.S.-Iran ceasefire talks\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/29/oil-prices-iran-ceasefire-us-trump-strait-hormuz-energy-costs.html\"},{\"title\":\"Brent oil price posts biggest monthly loss in six years as market counts on a U.S.-Iran deal\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/29/oil-price-iran-deal-war-ceasefire-trump.html\"},{\"title\":\"Oil prices fall after Trump says he will make final determination on Iran deal\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/amp/2026/05/29/oil-price-iran-deal-war-ceasefire-trump.html\"},{\"title\":\"Oil prices fall after Iran sends updated peace proposal to mediators in Pakistan\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/01/oil-prices-today-brent-wti-us-iran-war-trump-war-powers-deadline.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding the US-Iran 60-day ceasefire memorandum and its impact on oil prices:\n\n## The 60-Day Ceasefire Memorandum\n\nU.S. officials told CNBC Thursday that negotiators hammered out a 60-day memorandum of understanding, or MOU, to extend the ceasefire and start talks on Iran's nuclear program. Trump still has to sign off on the MOU, the officials said.\n\n## Oil Price Impact\n\nThe agreement has had a significant effect on oil markets:\n\n- Brent crude futures, the international benchmark, fell 58 cents to close at $93.71 per barrel.\n\n- Global oil prices have tumbled by around 20% from 2026 highs as investors have grown increasingly optimistic on prospects for a long-lasting ceasefire deal between the U.S. and Iran, which would unlock shipping through the Strait of Hormuz.\n\n- The international price benchmark has plunged almost 19% in May, having suffered its worst month since the Covid-19 pandemic, is now off about 20% from its 2026 peaks. Meanwhile, U.S. West Texas Intermediate futures prices have fallen 16.5% month-to-date, and were last seen almost 1.9% lower on Friday at $87.18.\n\nThe drop in oil prices reflects market optimism about the potential ceasefire agreement and the possibility of restoring normal shipping through the Strait of Hormuz.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"1b03cedc-d3e6-4fc2-b91f-759fdc967e0f","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:50.312Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
