{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BAAS2MP37M8wUXyhL6qAxq","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"copper price LME May 29 2026 weekly\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Copper - Price - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/commodity/copper\"},{\"title\":\"LME Copper | London Metal Exchange\",\"url\":\"https://www.lme.com/metals/non-ferrous/lme-copper\"},{\"title\":\"westmetall . market data . prices/lme stocks . copper, tin, lead, zinc, aluminium, nickel, gold, fine silver\",\"url\":\"https://www.westmetall.com/en/markdaten.php?action=averages&field=LME_Cu_cash\"},{\"title\":\"Price LME Copper May 2026 - August 2026 spread (official close) - Metal Radar\",\"url\":\"https://metalradar.com/price/copper/lme/may-2026-to-august-2026-spread/official-close\"},{\"title\":\"LME Copper Monthly Average May '26 Futures Price - Barchart.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.barchart.com/futures/quotes/L8CK26\"},{\"title\":\"LME Copper Monthly Average Futures | London Metal Exchange\",\"url\":\"https://www.lme.com/market-data/reports-and-data/commitments-of-traders/lme-copper-monthly-average-futures\"},{\"title\":\"Copper - Grade A - LME (London Metal Exchange) spot price - Price in dollars per metric ton | Insee\",\"url\":\"https://www.insee.fr/langue/en?url=%2Fen%2Fstatistiques%2Fserie%2F010002052\"},{\"title\":\"LME Copper Prices 2026 | ZAMAK\",\"url\":\"https://www.zamak.us/lme-copper-prices-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"LMEselect Copper 3 Month\",\"url\":\"https://www.metal.com/copper/LME_CA_3M\"},{\"title\":\"Copper Prices Are Forecast to Decline Somewhat from Record Highs in 2026 | Goldman Sachs\",\"url\":\"https://www.goldmansachs.com/insights/articles/copper-prices-forecast-to-decline-from-record-highs-in-2026\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about copper prices on the LME as of May 29, 2026:\n\nCopper futures fell below $6.25 per pound on Thursday from the one-week high of $6.4 earlier in the week. Additionally, copper futures held steady near $6.4 per pound on Friday and were on track to register a second straight monthly advance, underpinned by renewed optimism over demand linked to the global artificial intelligence expansion and the rapid build-out of data center infrastructure.\n\nThe price movements during this period were influenced by several factors: reports that the United States and Iran reached a preliminary peace agreement helped ease concerns about supply disruptions, further shaping market sentiment. On the supply side, production constraints in top producer Chile prompted major refiners to scale back capacity and output.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"c85d09a5-39ee-491d-b94b-d0719e4681f5","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:01:56.479Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Commodities & forex research"}
