{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Qd8UvG7SfGVeFFrQ7NhHpQ","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"EIA crude oil inventory report week May 2026 stockpiles draw build\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Weekly Petroleum Status Report - U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA)\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/petroleum/supply/weekly/\"},{\"title\":\"United States Crude Oil Inventories\",\"url\":\"https://www.investing.com/economic-calendar/eia-crude-oil-inventories-75\"},{\"title\":\"Crude oil inventories\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/petroleum/supply/weekly/pdf/highlights.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Oil Market Report - May 2026 – Analysis - IEA\",\"url\":\"https://www.iea.org/reports/oil-market-report-may-2026\"},{\"title\":\"EIA Reports Larger-Than-Expected Crude Oil Stockpile Draw | May 2026 - News and Statistics - IndexBox\",\"url\":\"https://www.indexbox.io/blog/us-crude-oil-inventories-fall-by-7863-million-barrels-exceeding-expectations/\"},{\"title\":\"U.S. Stocks of Crude Oil and Petroleum Products\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/dnav/pet/pet_stoc_wstk_dcu_nus_w.htm\"},{\"title\":\"This Week In Petroleum Crude Oil Section - U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA)\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/petroleum/weekly/crude.php\"},{\"title\":\"Petroleum & Other Liquids Data - U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA)\",\"url\":\"https://www.eia.gov/petroleum/data.php\"},{\"title\":\"United States Crude Oil Stocks Change\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/united-states/crude-oil-stocks-change\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what the EIA crude oil inventory reports show for May 2026:\n\n## Most Recent Report (Week Ending May 22, 2026)\n\nUS crude inventories fell by 3.327 million barrels in the week ended May 22, compared with expectations for a 4 million barrel draw. At 441.7 million barrels, U.S. crude oil inventories are about 2% below the five-year average for this time of year.\n\n## Earlier May 2026 Reports\n\nCrude oil inventory in the United States sank by 7.9 million barrels in the week ending May 15th to 445 million barrels, well above expectations of a 2.9 million draw. The reduction was combined with a 9.9 million barrel draw of the governments Strategic Petroleum Reserve.\n\nUS crude inventories fell by 4.306 million barrels to 452.9 million barrels in the week ended May 8, compared with expectations for a 2.1 million barrel draw.\n\nOverall, May 2026 has shown significant stockpile draws (decreases) across multiple weekly reports, with the most dramatic being in the week ending May 15th.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"30fa33d5-3aa4-4377-85c9-03733edf70cd","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:19.747Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Commodities & forex research"}
