th, on May 20, Ethereum spot ETFs recorded a $28.14 million net outflow, marking the eighth consecutive day of withdrawals, with ETHA experiencing the largest outflow at $30.94 million.\n\nDespite these outflows during specific periods, ETHA maintained significant cumulative net inflows of $11.67 billion as of May 20.\n\nThe broader May 2026 context shows that on May 1, U.S. spot Ethereum ETFs recorded $101.2 million in net inflows, with BlackRock clients purchasing $43.2 million through ETHA, suggesting that the month had mixed trading patterns with both inflows and outflows at different points.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"e304c6f8-3249-4f55-ae7f-5c698853eb66","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:21.332Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Crypto & alternative research"}
