 USDC Dominance\n\nUSDT holds $189.6B and USDC holds $77.6B in circulating supply as of April 29, 2026. USDT hit a new ATH of $190B, gaining $5.7B and reclaiming market share for the first time in four months, now at 59.2%. Circle's USDC stands in second place at about $76.4 billion. Together, USDT and USDC account for the vast majority of stablecoin value.\n\n## DeFi and Blockchain Infrastructure\n\nEthereum still anchors much of that activity. The network hosts around 55% of total stablecoin value, or roughly $190 billion, making it the main base layer for these dollar-linked assets.\n\n## Market Activity\n\nStablecoins accounted for 75% of the total crypto trading volume in Q1 2026, highlighting their crucial role in the crypto ecosystem.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"5bdd72c2-64d0-4aeb-ae62-958671880e00","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:23.377Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Crypto & alternative research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YGHJSKB32S7mdfVZD2FirT","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"wheat corn soybean coffee price late May 2026 weekly\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Farm Futures morning grain market analysis\",\"url\":\"https://www.farmprogress.com/markets-and-quotes/morning-market-review\"},{\"title\":\"Coffee - Price - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/commodity/coffee\"},{\"title\":\"Wheat, corn, soybean prices are below breakeven, signaling fourth year of losses | Capital Press\",\"url\":\"https://capitalpress.com/2026/05/08/wheat-corn-soybean-prices-are-below-breakeven-signaling-fourth-year-of-losses/\"},{\"title\":\"Detailed Grain Futures | Corn, Soybean, Wheat, Oats & Rice - Frontier Cooperative\",\"url\":\"https://www.frontiercooperative.com/grain/futures\"},{\"title\":\"Coffee Prices (1969-2026)\",\"url\":\"https://www.macrotrends.net/2535/coffee-prices-historical-chart-data\"},{\"title\":\"National Weekly Non-GMO/GE Grain Report\",\"url\":\"https://www.ams.usda.gov/mnreports/ams_2920.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Coffee Prices and Coffee Futures Prices - Barchart.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.barchart.com/futures/quotes/kc*0/futures-prices\"},{\"title\":\"Historical Corn, Soybean and Wheat Prices | FCSAmerica\",\"url\":\"https://www.fcsamerica.com/insurance/resources/crop-price-history\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about commodity prices in late May 2026:\n\n## Wheat Prices\nJuly SRW wheat rose 4.25 cents to $6.2675 after plunging 13 cents Wednesday to $6.2250, the contract's fifth consecutive decline and its lowest close since May 8. July HRW wheat fell 0.75 cent to $6.69 after sinking 6.5 cents Wednesday to $6.6975, a fifth straight daily loss and three-week low close.\n\n## Corn Prices\nJuly corn futures rose 4.5 cents to $4.57 per bushel late in overnight trading after earlier dropping to $4.5150, the lowest intraday price since April 14.\n\n## Soybean Prices\nJuly soybeans rose 9.5 cents to $11.9475 overnight after slipping 0.75 cent Wednesday to $11.8525, the contract's fifth drop in the past six days and its lowest close since May 15.\n\n## Coffee Prices\nCoffee fell to 265.60 USd/Lbs on May 29, 2026, down 3.15% from the previous day. Arabica coffee futures traded around $2.70 per pound, near their lowest since November 2024, on expectations of a bumper harvest in top grower Brazil.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"7321ab4f-3144-4e21-8894-67d91b9f26e0","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:23.433Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Commodities & forex research"}
