ion event saw $500 million in long positions wiped out across the crypto market, including a 5% drop for Solana (SOL) and XRP, triggered by a long-skewed market amidst a global bond selloff.\n\nMore recently, total liquidations reached $333.29 million in 24 hours, with longs making up nearly 85% of the wipeout, with Bitcoin leading at $116.17 million, followed by Ethereum at $53.18 million.\n\n## Bitcoin and Ethereum Movement\n\nBitcoin fell 1.4% to $75,247, Ethereum dropped 0.7% to $2,069, XRP slipped 0.5%, BNB lost 0.3%, and Hyperliquid's HYPE fell 3.0% on May 27. XRP is testing key support as bearish pressure builds across major cryptos as of May 30.\n\n## XRP and Altcoin Updates\n\nXRP ETFs took in $35 million while bitcoin and ether funds lost $2 billion from May 20 to May 29, indicating relative strength in XRP compared to Bitcoin and Ethereum. Additionally, a draft plan aims to add new liquidity models to XRPL, potentially boosting capital efficiency.\n\n## Institutional Activity\n\nGoldman Sachs' Q1 2026 Form 13F shows a complete liquidation of all XRP and Solana-related ETF positions, while Goldman kept its Bitcoin ETF allocation largely intact at around $700 million.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"905d984f-6f6a-4bf2-b6be-167419ae850c","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:23.743Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Crypto & alternative research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016NTRKFMZ19t67nFofpBhKj","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Baltic Dry Index freight rates tanker May 2026 Hormuz\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Baltic Exchange Dry Index - Price - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/commodity/baltic\"},{\"title\":\"Freightos Baltic Index (FBX): Freight Rate Container Price Index\",\"url\":\"https://www.freightos.com/enterprise/terminal/freightos-baltic-index-global-container-pricing-index/\"},{\"title\":\"The Strait of Hormuz and the Container Market: What You Need to Know\",\"url\":\"https://www.freightos.com/freight-industry-updates/market-updates/the-strait-of-hormuz-and-the-container-market-what-you-need-to-know/\"},{\"title\":\"Hormuz tension keeps pressure on rates; Section 122 invalidated - May 12, 2026 Update | Freightos\",\"url\":\"https://www.freightos.com/freight-industry-updates/weekly-freight-updates/hormuz-tension-keeps-pressure-on-rates-section-122-invalidated-may-12-2026-update/\"},{\"title\":\"Dry Bulk Market | Hellenic Shipping News Worldwide\",\"url\":\"https://www.hellenicshippingnews.com/category/dry-bulk-market/\"},{\"title\":\"Indices\",\"url\":\"https://www.balticexchange.com/en/data-services/market-information0/indices.html\"},{\"title\":\"Asia - Europe container rates slide, transpac more buoyant - May 5, 2026 Update | Freightos\",\"url\":\"https://www.freightos.com/freight-industry-updates/weekly-freight-updates/asia-europe-container-rates-slide-transpac-more-buoyant-may-5-2026-update/\"},{\"title\":\"Baltic Dry Index | 28 May 2026 - HandyBulk\",\"url\":\"https://www.handybulk.com/baltic-dry-index/\"},{\"title\":\"Baltic Exchange Dry Index (BDI) and Freight Rates\",\"url\":\"https://investmenttools.com/futures/bdi_baltic_dry_index.htm\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding freight rates and the Baltic Dry Index for May 2026:\n\n## Baltic Dry Index (May 2026)\n\nThe broader Baltic index gained 20% over the month of May. Throughout the month, the index experienced fluctuations:\n\n- On Wednesday, May 20, 2026, the Baltic Dry Index decreased by 49 points, reaching 3005 points\n- The index extended its decline into a fifth day, falling about 1.4% to its lowest since May 5 at 2,964 points\n\n## Tanker and Hormuz Situation\n\nThe search results show that Baltic Exchange tanker assessments are published on both Worldscale and Time Charter Equivalent basis, though specific tanker rate data for May 2026 was not prominently featured in the results.\n\nRegarding the Strait of Hormuz, global business surveys in May 2026 are expected to show expanded manufactured goods stockpiling as industries front-load inventory to insulate against a three-month Middle East energy crisis that threatens to accelerate worldwide pipeline inflation. Transpacific rates were up about $1,000/FEU compared to before the war, while Asia – Europe prices that climbed by a few hundred dollars per FEU in March have mostly slipped back to pre-war levels.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"3414e8a1-1c60-4526-81f4-258340c27715","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:23.960Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Commodities & forex research"}
