{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0182yFK5aeHkq7AK8eQPe5j4","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"space stocks Rocket Lab RKLB Planet Labs Intuitive Machines May 2026 weekly\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Intuitive Machines Rallies 9%, Rocket Lab and Planet Labs Decline in Space Stock Divergence - 24/7 Wall St.\",\"url\":\"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/28/intuitive-machines-rallies-9-rocket-lab-and-planet-labs-decline-in-space-stock-divergence/\"},{\"title\":\"Rocket Lab Sinks 9%, Planet Labs Tumbles 6%, Intuitive Machines Slides 5%: Space Rally Hits a Wall - 24/7 Wall St.\",\"url\":\"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/19/rocket-lab-sinks-9-planet-labs-tumbles-6-intuitive-machines-slides-5-space-rally-hits-a-wall/\"},{\"title\":\"Rocket Lab Stock Is Up 30% Today: Is It Outperforming Other Space Stocks Like Intuitive Machines and Planet Labs? - 24/7 Wall St.\",\"url\":\"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/08/rocket-lab-stock-is-up-30-today-is-it-outperforming-other-space-stocks-like-intuitive-machines-and-planet-labs/\"},{\"title\":\"AST SpaceMobile Jumps 7%, Rocket Lab Climbs 6%, Planet Labs Rises 4%: Space Stocks Resume Their Climb - 24/7 Wall St.\",\"url\":\"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/22/ast-spacemobile-jumps-7-rocket-lab-climbs-6-planet-labs-rises-4-space-stocks-resume-their-climb/\"},{\"title\":\"Why space stocks like Planet Labs, Rocket Lab, and LUNR are surging this year\",\"url\":\"https://invezz.com/news/2026/05/26/why-space-stocks-like-planet-labs-rocket-lab-and-lunr-are-surging-this-year/\"},{\"title\":\"Rocket Lab Sinks 9%, Planet Labs Tumbles 6%, Intuitive Machines Slides 5%: Space Rally Hits a Wall\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/rocket-lab-sinks-9-planet-153206806.html\"},{\"title\":\"Rocket Lab Sinks 9%, Planet Labs Tumbles 6%, Intuitive Machines Slides 5%: Space Rally Hits a Wall - AOL\",\"url\":\"https://www.aol.com/finance/rocket-lab-sinks-9-planet-153206106.html\"},{\"title\":\"Space Stocks RKLB, ASTS, LUNR: Buy, Hold, or Wait for SpaceX IPO?\",\"url\":\"https://www.heygotrade.com/en/blog/space-stocks-rklb-asts-lunr-spacex-ipo/\"},{\"title\":\"Intuitive Machines Rallies 9%, Rocket Lab and Planet Labs Decline in Space Stock Divergence\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/intuitive-machines-rallies-9-rocket-150011417.html\"},{\"title\":\"Rocket Lab (RKLB) Stock Price & Overview\",\"url\":\"https://stockanalysis.com/stocks/rklb/\"}]\n\nHere are the latest developments in space stocks for May 2026:\n\n## Week Overview\n\nRocket Lab (RKLB) stock is down as the company faces direct competition with SpaceX in small and medium-lift launches, while Planet Labs (PL) stock is down 2% after a 146% year-to-date surge based on Earth observation imagery and analytics revenue. In contrast, Intuitive Machines (NASDAQ:LUNR) stock is up 9% in mid-morning trading Thursday, while Rocket Lab stock is down 3% and Planet Labs stock is lower by 2%.\n\n## Performance Context\n\nThe recent declines should be viewed with perspective on the year-to-date performance: LUNR stock is up 166% YTD, RKLB stock is up 106% YTD, and PL stock has gained 146% YTD. Investors are rotating capital within the space sector after SpaceX's IPO announcement, with traders treating weakness in Rocket Lab stock and Planet Labs stock as profit-taking from extreme valuations rather than a fundamental shift in the space infrastructure thesis.\n\n## Company-Specific Highlights\n\n**Rocket Lab:** The company's Q1 2026 revenue came in at $200.35 million, up 64% year over year, and Rocket Lab exited the quarter with a record $2.2 billion backlog. RKLB stock is up 49% over the past month as Neutron's debut later this year approaches.\n\n**Planet Labs:** Planet Labs stock is rising rapidly, based in part on the company's remaining performance obligations jumping 361% to $672.47M; this is driven by defense and intelligence contracts with the NGA, NRO, NASA, the U.S. Navy, and NATO.\n\n**Intuitive Machines:** The company is focused on lunar exploration and space services, anchored by NASA Commercial Lunar Payload Services task orders and a U.S. Space Force contract pipeline.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"67ed2c47-2685-49af-8a87-699f04b67d56","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:27.738Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
