{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0192VL5qsB2hnWMmhn8M6NrD","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"rare earth critical minerals stocks MP Materials lithium May 2026 week China\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"China's Stranglehold on Critical Minerals Creates Massive Opportunity in These 5 Stocks - 24/7 Wall St.\",\"url\":\"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/01/26/chinas-stranglehold-on-critical-minerals-creates-massive-opportunity-in-these-5-stocks/\"},{\"title\":\"The Best Rare-Earth Stock to Buy and Hold for the Next Decade | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/05/12/the-best-rare-earth-stock-to-buy-and-hold-for-the/\"},{\"title\":\"Rare Earth Investment 2026: Best Western Supply Chain ...\",\"url\":\"https://intellectia.ai/blog/rare-earth-investment-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Best Rare Earth Stocks to Buy Now May 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.zacks.com/featured-articles/321/best-rare-earth-stocks\"},{\"title\":\"Rare Earth Stocks to Watch After China's 45% Price Increase | Best Rare Earth Stocks 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.canadianminingreport.com/blog/rare-earth-stocks-to-watch-after-china-s-45-price-increase\"},{\"title\":\"5 Top Rare Earth Stocks and 3 Mining Infrastructure Plays in 2026 - MarketWise\",\"url\":\"https://marketwise.com/investing/rare-earth-stocks-ai-mining-infrastructure-plays/\"},{\"title\":\"Best Rare Earth Stocks to Buy Now in 2026 | VectorVest\",\"url\":\"https://www.vectorvest.com/blog/stockmarket/best-rare-earth-stocks/\"},{\"title\":\"Forget MP Materials. One of These Mining Stocks Is Up 274% and Has $354 Million in Pentagon Contracts. The Other Controls the Largest Rare Earth Deposit Outside China - 24/7 Wall St.\",\"url\":\"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/15/forget-mp-materials-one-of-these-mining-stocks-is-up-274-and-has-354-million-in-pentagon-contracts-the-other-controls-the-largest-rare-earth-deposit-outside-china/\"},{\"title\":\"China’s Stranglehold on Critical Minerals Creates Massive Opportunity in These 5 Stocks\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/china-stranglehold-critical-minerals-creates-142809584.html\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what's happening with rare earth critical minerals stocks, MP Materials, lithium, and China in May 2026:\n\n## Rare Earth and Critical Minerals Market\n\nRare-earth elements are vital for energy and national security, and China currently dominates the global supply. The Trump-Xi summit in May 2026 brought rare earth supply chains to the forefront of strategic discussions between the world's two largest economies, with rare earth emerging as a critical pressure point with immediate economic implications.\n\n## MP Materials Performance\n\nMP Materials stock appreciated over 30% in the past month ahead of strong first-quarter 2026 earnings. MP Materials is currently the only large-scale producer of rare-earth elements in the Western Hemisphere, owning Mountain Pass, one of the world's highest-grade rare-earth mineral deposits.\n\nMP Materials expects to begin magnet sales from its Independence facility in the second half of 2026, marking the company's transition from a concentrate producer to a downstream manufacturer of high-value rare earth magnets.\n\n## Lithium Market Activity\n\nThe 45% Q2 2026 hike in rare earth prices reflects structural imbalances in the market. Export quotas and controls could displace up to 13,000 tonnes of demand annually to non-Chinese sources in 2026 alone.\n\n## Government Support and Strategy\n\nIn February, the U.S. launched Project Vault, a $12 billion initiative to create a strategic reserve of 60 critical minerals vital to economic and national security. The U.S. Department of Defense invested $400 million in preferred stock in MP Materials and holds a 15% stake; the government will pay MP a minimum of $110/kg for NdPr oxide, and for 10 years following the construction of the 10X facility, the U.S. government will ensure that 100% of the magnets produced will be purchased by defense and commercial customers.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"cc0dc1b5-a6a4-4d8d-b798-2e70ae0ff4d7","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:40.386Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FvrqmnMQuNy6BdbMVn5Y7y","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"robotics stocks Tesla Optimus Symbotic Intuitive Surgical May 2026 week\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"8 Best Robotics Stocks to Buy in 2026 | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/market-sectors/information-technology/robotics-stocks/\"},{\"title\":\"Forget Tesla. The Robotics Company Actually Shipping Revenue Has a $22 Billion Backlog and Nobody Is Talking About It - 24/7 Wall St.\",\"url\":\"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/19/forget-tesla-the-robotics-company-actually-shipping-revenue-has-a-22-billion-backlog-and-nobody-is-talking-about-it/\"},{\"title\":\"Best Robotics Stocks to Buy: Compare TSLA, ISRG & SYM - TipRanks.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.tipranks.com/compare-stocks/robotics-automation-stocks\"},{\"title\":\"Top Three Robotics Stocks to Watch in 2026 - MarketWise\",\"url\":\"https://marketwise.com/investing/trumps-robotics-push-top-robotics-stocks/\"},{\"title\":\"LevelFields — Best Robotics Stocks to Watch in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.levelfields.ai/news/best-robotics-stocks-to-watch-in-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Top Robotics Stocks 2026: TER & TSLA Leaders - TipRanks.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.tipranks.com/compare-stocks/robotics-autonomous-systems\"},{\"title\":\"5 Best Robotics Stocks to Buy in 2026 | Investing | U.S. News\",\"url\":\"https://money.usnews.com/investing/articles/5-best-robotics-stocks-to-buy-right-now\"},{\"title\":\"The Robotics Stock Nobody's Talking About Already Has a $23 Billion Backlog | InvestorPlace\",\"url\":\"https://investorplace.com/smartmoney/2026/05/robotics-stock-23-billion-backlog/\"},{\"title\":\"10 Best Robotics Stocks to Buy in 2026: AI, Automation & Humanoids\",\"url\":\"https://traderfactor.com/10-best-robotics-stocks-to-buy-in-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Outlook 2026: Three Robotics Stocks Powering Ahead | CMC Markets\",\"url\":\"https://www.cmcmarkets.com/en/optox/outlook-2026-three-robotics-stocks-powering-ahead\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results for robotics stocks in May 2026, here's what I found:\n\n## Tesla (TSLA) and Optimus\n\nIn 2026, Tesla stopped producing its Model S sedan and Model X crossover to free up factory space and turn its Fremont, CA, factory into an Optimus robot plant. Construction is officially underway on a dedicated Optimus factory expansion at Gigafactory Texas. Tesla's long-term Optimus production target at the new factory is reportedly up to 10 million robots per year.\n\nRecent stock prices show Tesla's stock price is currently $422.24, and its average 12-month price target is $403.86.\n\n## Symbotic (SYM)\n\nSymbotic carries a contracted backlog of $22.70 billion, signed business that translates into multi-year revenue visibility. Q2 FY2026 revenue rose 23.1% year over year to $676.48 million, with 70 systems deployed against 46 a year earlier.\n\nSymbotic's stock price is currently $47.32, and its average 12-month price target is $67.63.\n\n## Intuitive Surgical (ISRG)\n\nIntuitive Surgical is a pioneer of robotic-assisted surgery. Its da Vinci system made its commercial debut in 2000 and has since expanded worldwide. Intuitive Surgical's stock price is currently $421.12, and its average 12-month price target is $576.53.\n\nThe search results highlight that while Tesla is pursuing ambitious humanoid robot plans, Symbotic is already generating significant revenue from its warehouse automation systems with a substantial contracted backlog.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"17ade86d-35bb-470f-a094-294869cc22b9","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:40.393Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
