{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TLMjG3N6Rd7GPymjVou3gS","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"energy storage Fluence Tesla QuantumScape battery stocks May 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"QuantumScape Corp - Form DEF 14A - FY2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001811414/000119312526173828/qs-20260423.htm\"},{\"title\":\"QuantumScape Corp - Form 8-K - FY2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001811414/000119312526170507/qs-ex99_1.htm\"},{\"title\":\"QuantumScape Corp - Form 8-K - FY2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001811414/000119312526046623/qs-ex99_1.htm\"},{\"title\":\"QuantumScape Corp - Form 10-Q - FY2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001811414/000119312526177161/qs-20260331.htm\"},{\"title\":\"QuantumScape Corp - Form ARS - FY2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001811414/000119312526174000/qs_ars_2026.pdf\"}]\n\nI found relevant SEC filings for QuantumScape. Let me search for information on Fluence and Tesla energy storage stocks for May 2026.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Fluence Energy, Inc. (FLNC) Stock Price, News, Quote & History - Yahoo Finance\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/FLNC/\"},{\"title\":\"Fluence Energy Inc Stock Price Today | NASDAQ: FLNC Live - Investing.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.investing.com/equities/fluence-energy\"},{\"title\":\"FLNC Stock Price, News & Analysis | Fluence Energy\",\"url\":\"https://www.stocktitan.net/overview/FLNC/\"},{\"title\":\"Fluence Energy Stock Spikes 100% After Battery Storage Firm Beats Earnings Estimates | TIKR.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.tikr.com/blog/fluence-energy-stock-spikes-100-after-battery-storage-firm-beats-earnings-estimates\"},{\"title\":\"Stock Information | Fluence\",\"url\":\"https://ir.fluenceenergy.com/stock-information\"},{\"title\":\"Fluence Energy (FLNC) Stock Forecast: Analyst Ratings, Predictions & Price Target 2026\",\"url\":\"https://public.com/stocks/flnc/forecast-price-target\"},{\"title\":\"FLNC Stock Price Quote | Morningstar\",\"url\":\"https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/xnas/flnc/quote\"},{\"title\":\"Fluence Energy (FLNC) Stock Price & Overview\",\"url\":\"https://stockanalysis.com/stocks/flnc/\"},{\"title\":\"FLNC Stock Price, Quote & Chart | FLUENCE ENERGY INC (NASDAQ:FLNC) | ChartMill.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.chartmill.com/stock/quote/FLNC/profile\"},{\"title\":\"Fluence Energy signs master supply agreements with two ‘major’ hyperscalers | Utility Dive\",\"url\":\"https://www.utilitydive.com/news/fluence-energy-signs-master-supply-agreements-with-two-major-hyperscalers/820016/\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Tesla, Inc. (TSLA) Stock Price, News, Quote & History - Yahoo Finance\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/TSLA/\"},{\"title\":\"Tesla Inc (TSLA) Stock Price & News - Google Finance\",\"url\":\"https://www.google.com/finance/beta/quote/TSLA:NASDAQ\"},{\"title\":\"Tesla (TSLA Stock) Sparks $2.1B Samsung Battery Deal as Global EV Demand Charges Ahead\",\"url\":\"https://carboncredits.com/tesla-tsla-stock-sparks-2-1b-samsung-battery-deal-as-global-ev-demand-charges-ahead/\"},{\"title\":\"TSLA: Tesla Inc - Stock Price, Quote and News - CNBC\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/quotes/TSLA\"},{\"title\":\"Tesla\",\"url\":\"https://www.tesla.com/megapack\"},{\"title\":\"Powerwall – Home Battery Storage | Tesla\",\"url\":\"https://www.tesla.com/powerwall\"},{\"title\":\"Tesla energy storage se - Stocks\",\"url\":\"https://www.tradingview.com/symbols/BME-TES/\"}]\n\nBased on my web search results, here's what I found regarding energy storage stocks in May 2026:\n\n## **Fluence Energy (FLNC)**\n\nAs of May 7, 2026, Fluence Energy (FLNC) is trading at a price of 18.41 USD, though prices fluctuated throughout May. Fluence Energy stock surged roughly 100% after it posted fiscal second-quarter results that topped Wall Street's expectations, with two major banks HSBC and Roth Capital upgrading FLNC stock following the report, citing the company's improving profitability and strong order momentum.\n\nThe company's energy storage products include Gridstack Pro, a large-scale front-of-the-meter application; Gridstack, a front-of-the-meter application; Ultrastack for critical system requirements of distribution and transmission networks; Smartstack, a split architecture design, incorporating embedded intelligence and higher energy density compared to traditional AC systems.\n\n## **QuantumScape (QS)**\n\nOn July 5, 2024, QuantumScape entered into a Collaboration Agreement with PowerCo SE, a battery cell company wholly owned by Volkswagen, with the goal of industrializing the solid-state lithium-metal battery technology for their first planned product—the QSE-5. In 2026, QuantumScape aims to seize opportunities where its differentiated solid-state technology can capture significant value, focused on further advancements to meet the ever-growing need for energy storage in existing and emerging applications.\n\n## **Tesla (TSLA)**\n\nTesla sells lithium-ion battery energy storage products, such as Powerwall and Megapack, energy generation products, including solar panels and solar roof. Global energy storage capacity is expected to grow tenfold by the end of the decade.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"50432a6f-ed40-45f3-ac27-946882ff879b","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:48.681Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015VaNb1jtueU2vFHbnsuDCd","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"bond market rally week May 29 2026 Treasury yields fall Iran ceasefire de-escalation\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"US Bonds Gain in Catch-Up Trade as Trump Sees Iran Progress - Bloomberg\",\"url\":\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-05-26/treasuries-rally-as-trump-signals-progress-in-iran-negotiations\"},{\"title\":\"Treasury yields tick lower as investors stay optimistic on Iran peace deal prospects despite U.S. strikes\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/27/treasury-yields-investor-optimism-ceasefire-prospects-rise.html\"},{\"title\":\"Near record highs, stocks face fresh test from bond yields | CNN Business\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnn.com/2026/05/26/business/us-stocks-bond-yields\"},{\"title\":\"Stocks & Bonds Rise After US-Iran Deal Reports | The Close 5/28/2026 - YouTube\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OxMYC4weSiU\"},{\"title\":\"Treasury yields slide after Memorial Day break as traders weigh Iran peace prospects\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/26/treasury-yields-us-strikes-on-iran-oil-bonds.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what happened in the bond market during the week of May 29, 2026:\n\n## Bond Market Rally and Treasury Yields\n\nTreasury yields fell on Tuesday as bond markets returned from a Memorial Day break to bolstered hopes of a Middle East peace deal, even as the U.S. military conducted fresh strikes on Iran. Specifically, the yield on the 10-year U.S. Treasury note moved lower by more than 8 basis points to 4.489%, with the 2-year Treasury note yield dropping more than 8 basis points to 4.04% and the longer-dated 30-year Treasury bond yield declining more than 5 basis points to 5.024%.\n\n## Iran De-escalation\n\nTreasuries rose as investors reacted to oil price declines after US President Donald Trump said peace negotiations with Iran were proceeding, though negotiations were described as \"proceeding nicely.\" \n\nOil prices fell Wednesday as traders hoped for progress on peace negotiations between the U.S. and Iran, with Brent crude futures closing down 5.31% to $94.29 per barrel, while U.S. West Texas Intermediate crude futures lost 5.55% to settle at $88.68 a barrel.\n\n## Broader Market Context\n\nGlobal sovereign bond markets broadly rallied on Wednesday.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"91e4feab-6fe1-4966-a0a4-b4cac1530991","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:49.006Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SEfRuzyqLPcTrMwBsZ3ox2","type":"tool_result","content":"# Crypto Market Weekly Recap – May 30, 2026\n\n**Publication Date:** May 30, 2026\n\n## Bitcoin Price & Key Levels\nBitcoin dropped to **$72,500** during the week, representing a significant decline from earlier levels. The article notes BTC moved below $73,000 amid institutional pressure.\n\n## Bitcoin ETF Flows\nSpot Bitcoin ETFs experienced **$1.42 billion in outflows** since May 25, marking ten consecutive days of outflows—the first such streak since 2024. Morgan Stanley's Bitcoin ETF turned negative on May 29 with **$5.26 million in outflows**.\n\n## Ethereum Bearish Range\nEthereum fell below the **$2,000 psychological support** on May 28. Analyst Ali Martinez warned that \"Ethereum will drop to $1,560 if it makes a weekly close below $1,850.\" The RSI reading of 31 indicates oversold territory.\n\n## XRP Spot Bid Surge\nXRP experienced a significant bid-side imbalance with **seven times more bid orders than sell orders**, though the long/short ratio remained negative since May 3, suggesting bears still outnumber bulls despite retail enthusiasm around Stellar's (XLM) 33% rally.\n\n## Market Context\nThe crypto market shed **$150 billion in market cap** over six days as institutional demand weakened and retail traders remained largely absent."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"c21aeff4-dea4-42ba-bfe3-d8745bef2b56","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:49.984Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Crypto & alternative research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LezRjiYJgTyQM9Pp7yeKg7","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Fed officials speeches week May 26 2026 Powell Logan inflation interest rates hawkish\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - 2026 Speeches\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/speech/2026-speeches.htm\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - Speeches and Testimony of Federal Reserve Officials\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/speeches.htm\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - News & Events\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents.htm\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - Calendar\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/calendar.htm\"},{\"title\":\"WATCH: Fed Chair Powell holds news briefing after interest rate left unchanged | PBS News\",\"url\":\"https://www.pbs.org/newshour/economy/watch-live-fed-chair-powell-holds-news-briefing-after-latest-interest-rate-decision\"},{\"title\":\"US Fed holds rates steady, Powell to remain on its board | Business and Economy News | Al Jazeera\",\"url\":\"https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2026/4/29/us-fed-holds-rates-steady-in-powells-final-meeting-as-fed-chair\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell speaks after Fed holds interest rates steady — 4/29/26 - YouTube\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zKBz1WGsn6g\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - Federal Reserve issues FOMC statement\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/pressreleases/monetary20260429a.htm\"},{\"title\":\"A Few Words for the New Year - FEDERAL RESERVE BANK of NEW YORK\",\"url\":\"https://www.newyorkfed.org/newsevents/speeches/2026/wil260112\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about Fed officials' statements and policy decisions, though the most relevant content is from late April 2026 rather than specifically the week of May 26, 2026.\n\nHere's what I found regarding Fed officials and their stance on inflation and interest rates:\n\n**Recent Fed Policy Decision (April 29, 2026):**\n\nThe Committee decided to maintain the target range for the federal funds rate at 3‑1/2 to 3‑3/4 percent.\n\n**Hawkish Positions:**\n\nLorie K. Logan, who supported maintaining the target range for the federal funds rate but did not support inclusion of an easing bias in the statement at this time, indicating a more hawkish stance. This suggests Logan took a harder line against signaling future rate cuts.\n\n**Inflation Concerns:**\n\nInflation is elevated, in part reflecting the recent increase in global energy prices. Fed officials now forecast that inflation will be 2.7% at the end of this year, up from their December forecast but slightly below the 2.8% it reached in January. They expect core inflation, which excludes the volatile food and energy categories, to also finish the year at 2.7%, up from a previous forecast of 2.5%.\n\nThe search results don't contain specific speeches from the week of May 26, 2026. For more current information about Fed officials' speeches during that specific week, you may want to check the Federal Reserve Board's official events calendar or individual Federal Reserve bank websites.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"dcee3a1b-3904-4ef9-863f-537c2612c7dd","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:50.517Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
