{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016aUDazFaxzyZw1X1hEiRWG","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"crypto hack exploit depeg May 30 2026 weekend stablecoin DeFi\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Biggest DeFi Hacks and Exploits of 2026: $1 Billion+ Lost and Counting\",\"url\":\"https://www.ccn.com/education/crypto/defi-hacks-exploits-causes-crypto-stolen-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"The Latest Stablecoin Hack Is a Reminder That ‘Digital Dollars’ Can Still Break\",\"url\":\"https://gizmodo.com/the-latest-stablecoin-hack-is-a-reminder-that-digital-dollars-can-still-break-2000763481\"},{\"title\":\"Resolv Labs' USR Stablecoin Depegs After $80M Exploit, Attacker Cashes Out Millions\",\"url\":\"https://coinalertnews.com/news/2026/03/22/resolv-stablecoin-exploit-depeg-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Crypto Hacks and DeFi Runs - Bank Policy Institute\",\"url\":\"https://bpi.com/crypto-hacks-and-defi-runs/\"},{\"title\":\"DeFi Hacks & Exploits Database - DefiLlama\",\"url\":\"https://defillama.com/hacks\"},{\"title\":\"Every Major DeFi Hack in 2026 So Far | Bridge Exploits Dominate\",\"url\":\"https://phemex.com/blogs/defi-hacks-2026-bridge-exploits-explained\"},{\"title\":\"400M+ Lost to DeFi Exploits in 2026 — Drift Protocol, Rhea Finance, Step Finance Among Biggest Hacks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ccn.com/education/crypto/defi-hacks-2026-137m-lost-step-finance-truebit-resolv-exploits/\"},{\"title\":\"The $292 million Kelp crypto exploit: how it happened, and what it means for DeFi\",\"url\":\"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/04/19/the-usd292-million-kelp-exploit-how-it-happened-and-what-it-means-for-defi\"},{\"title\":\"Wall Street’s trillion-dollar dilemma: Why AI-powered hackers are keeping big banks off the blockchain\",\"url\":\"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/05/28/defi-vulnerabilities-are-tradfi-biggest-blocker-as-protocols-hit-by-near-daily-exploits-certik\"},{\"title\":\"The $292M crypto hack exposed DeFi's weak spots. Here’s what must change, insiders say\",\"url\":\"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/05/02/the-usd292m-crypto-hack-exposed-defi-s-weak-spots-here-s-what-must-change-insiders-say\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what happened with crypto hacks and stablecoin depegging around the May 30, 2026 weekend:\n\n## StablR Stablecoin Hack (May 24-26, 2026 Weekend)\n\nEuropean stablecoin issuer StablR faced a security incident over the weekend that led to the creation of $13.5 million in unbacked stablecoins, though the attackers were only able to get away with around $2.8 million in net proceeds from the hack.\n\nThe breach took place on the Ethereum network through StablR's minting multisignature wallet. That wallet used a 1-of-3 threshold, meaning a single authorized signer could approve transactions. The attacker compromised one private key, added themselves as an administrator, and removed the legitimate operators before going on to mint roughly 8.35 million USDR (StableR's dollar-pegged stablecoin) and 4.5 million EURR (the company's euro-backed stablecoin).\n\nBlockchain security firms Blockaid and GoPlus Security both described the root cause as a security setup and key-management failure rather than any flaw in the smart contract code itself.\n\n## Broader 2026 DeFi Exploit Context\n\nBeyond this specific weekend incident, 2026 has been particularly challenging for DeFi. April has been the worse month in four years in terms of DeFi exploits. Near-daily hacks—many accelerated by AI and targeting smart contracts, oracles and cross-chain bridges—are a major barrier to large-scale institutional adoption.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"96071d67-d0a5-4507-a454-1ced8f2a3673","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:51.990Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Crypto & alternative research"}
