{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RJxrXCkBGHmL87MREmZNzH","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"May 31\" 2026 Iran Hormuz Trump deal oil weekend latest\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Brent oil jumps more than 3% after Iran vows to retaliate for U.S. strikes\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/26/oil-prices-today-brent-wti-iran-trump-hormuz.html\"},{\"title\":\"Oil prices turn lower as U.S.-Iran ceasefire extension awaits Trump approval\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/28/oil-prices-us-strikes-in-iran-revive-strait-of-hormuz-turmoil-fears.html\"},{\"title\":\"May 29-30, 2026 — US military ready to resume combat in Gulf if needed, defense secretary warns | CNN\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnn.com/2026/05/29/world/live-news/iran-trump-war-news\"},{\"title\":\"US-Iran talks are heating up again. But the danger isn’t over for gas prices | CNN Business\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnn.com/2026/05/26/business/oil-gas-iran-trump-deal\"},{\"title\":\"Trump ends Iran meeting without announcing ‘final determination’ on deal\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/29/trump-iran-deal-hormuz-nuclear-war.html\"},{\"title\":\"Oil prices fall after Trump indicates US-Iran deal possible\",\"url\":\"https://www.axios.com/2026/05/24/oil-prices-iran-war-hormuz-strait-trump-tehran-peace-talks\"},{\"title\":\"Oil prices post weekly loss as U.S. and Iran signal progress toward a deal\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/22/oil-prices-today-trump-iran-strait-of-hormuz-uranium-.html\"},{\"title\":\"Oil drops 20% from 2026 peak on optimism over U.S.-Iran ceasefire talks\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/29/oil-prices-iran-ceasefire-us-trump-strait-hormuz-energy-costs.html\"}]\n\nBased on the latest search results, here's what's happening regarding Iran, Hormuz, Trump, and oil as of May 31, 2026:\n\n## Deal Status\n\nThe U.S. and Iran are understood to have \"mostly agreed\" on the terms of a 60-day memorandum of understanding to extend the ceasefire, though the deal still needs sign-off from President Donald Trump. However, President Donald Trump ended a meeting in the White House Situation Room without announcing his final decision on whether to approve a deal to pause the three-month-old Iran war.\n\n## Key Sticking Points\n\nOn Friday, President Donald Trump made a series of demands — on the Strait of Hormuz, Iran's nuclear program and the unfreezing of Iranian assets held overseas - that did not go down well in Tehran. Specifically, Iran \"must agree\" to never have a nuclear weapon, and the Strait of Hormuz must be \"immediately open\" to unrestricted shipping traffic, with no tolls being imposed, Trump demanded.\n\n## Oil Prices\n\nBrent crude was down 1.2% on the final trading day of the month, at $92.56. The international price benchmark has plunged almost 19% in May, having suffered its worst month since the Covid-19 pandemic, is now off about 20% from its 2026 peaks.\n\n## Military Situation\n\nThe US military is ready to resume combat in the Gulf if required and is more strongly placed to do so than on day one of the conflict, according to US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"3b25aba3-36bb-4964-8a62-0a103b4c4779","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:52.821Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Commodities & forex research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ExNWDZQFHv6vZwPXvJbwhj","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Bitcoin US Iran tensions truce May 29 2026 risk assets market\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Bitcoin drops below $73,000 as U.S. strikes on Iran spark $1 billion liquidations\",\"url\":\"https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/05/28/bitcoin-drops-below-usd73-000-as-us-strikes-on-iran-spark-usd1-billion-liquidations\"},{\"title\":\"Bitcoin and ethereum prices today, Friday, May 29, 2026: Prices open lower, despite news of U.S.-Iran truce\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/personal-finance/investing/article/bitcoin-and-ethereum-prices-today-friday-may-29-2026-prices-open-lower-despite-news-of-us-iran-truce-115046286.html\"},{\"title\":\"Bitcoin, Altcoins Weaken as Iran Ceasefire Hopes Clash With Middle East Tensions\",\"url\":\"https://en.bloomingbit.io/feed/news/113134\"},{\"title\":\"Bitcoin rises near $74k after 7-wk low on Iran truce extension hopes By Investing.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.investing.com/news/cryptocurrency-news/bitcoin-rises-near-74k-after-7wk-low-on-iran-truce-extension-hopes-4715939\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Iran conflict: Impact on oil, gold, bitcoin, and forex markets | Fundamental analysis | OANDA | US\",\"url\":\"https://www.oanda.com/us-en/trade-tap-blog/analysis/fundamental/2026-iran-conflict-oil-gold-bitcoin-forex-impact/\"},{\"title\":\"Bitcoin Price Risks More Downside Amid Escalating Iran Situation - The Coin Republic\",\"url\":\"https://www.thecoinrepublic.com/2026/05/27/bitcoin-price-risks-more-downside-amid-escalating-iran-situation/\"},{\"title\":\"Bitcoin News Today (BTC) – Latest Updates & Trends\",\"url\":\"https://www.coinbird.com/cryptocurrencies/bitcoin/news\"},{\"title\":\"US and Iran trade military strikes as fragile ceasefire crumbles, crypto markets reel | Bitget News\",\"url\":\"https://www.bitget.com/amp/news/detail/12560605433050\"},{\"title\":\"Bitcoin Stuck in Range Struggle, Can US-Iran Conflict Help a Breakout?\",\"url\":\"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/cryptocurrencies/btc/261637746-bitcoin-btc-price-us-iran-israel-war-tradingkey\"},{\"title\":\"Weekly Crypto Recap: Bitcoin Falls on Iran Tensions as Tokenized Assets, US Regulation, and Network Upgrades Take Center Stage - Millionero Magazine | Crypto News | Futures\",\"url\":\"https://blog.millionero.com/blog/weekly-crypto-recap-bitcoin-falls-on-iran-tensions-as-tokenized-assets-us-regulation-and-network-upgrades-take-center-stage/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what happened with Bitcoin, US-Iran tensions, and risk assets around May 29, 2026:\n\n## Market Response to US-Iran Tensions and Truce News\n\nBitcoin fell below $73,000 amid U.S. airstrikes on Iran, with the strikes near the Strait of Hormuz and new U.S. sanctions triggering a broad sell-off in cryptocurrencies and other risk assets.\n\n## Bitcoin's Recovery on Truce Hopes\n\nBitcoin briefly recovered to $74,000 on May 29 as markets absorbed President Trump's claim that the Strait of Hormuz could reopen this weekend, pending an Iran deal. However, bitcoin and ethereum opened at their lowest levels all week, but the stage is set for the cryptocurrencies to rise in value after reports that a 60-day truce extension with Iran is on the president's desk awaiting his signature.\n\n## Cautious Market Sentiment\n\nDespite the truce news, the market is reflecting both the risk of further escalation and hopes for a truce, which has kept markets cautious rather than sparking a strong relief rally. US Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent said Iran must accept denuclearization and guarantee free passage through the Strait of Hormuz, signaling that negotiations have not been fully wrapped up.\n\n## Impact on Risk Assets\n\nThe easing of Middle East tensions helped lift global equities and pressured oil prices lower, encouraging traders to rotate back into higher-risk assets, including cryptocurrencies. Oil flows through the strait represent about 20% of global petroleum consumption, and a reopening could lower the oil-inflation premium that has weighed on risk assets.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"a4aed432-bd24-4d87-a418-9aab39ee9095","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:02:53.129Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Crypto & alternative research"}
