{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012LtD6Vfsm8koBDqBV7SwpE","type":"tool_result","content":"# Weekly Crypto Recap Summary (May 30, 2026)\n\n## Bitcoin Performance & Price Action\nBitcoin experienced significant downward pressure, dropping to $72,000 amid geopolitical tensions. Bitcoin ETFs saw cumulative weekly outflows of $1.42 billion, with BlackRock's IBIT recording its largest daily outflow since launch at $527.8 million on May 27. Approximately $1 billion in liquidations occurred, primarily from long positions. The Bitcoin Risk Index reached 33/100, classified as \"High Risk,\" with comparisons drawn to warning signals preceding the 2022 crash.\n\n## US-Iran Tensions Impact\nEscalating US-Iran tensions triggered market liquidations and heightened caution toward high-risk assets. However, US equities rallied on de-escalation hopes, with the Dow Jones, S&P 500, and Nasdaq reaching all-time highs while the VIX fell. The Treasury Department seized nearly $1 billion in Iran-linked crypto assets.\n\n## Tokenized Assets & RWA Growth\n- Stellar (XLM) surged 50% following DTCC's announcement of integration plans with its tokenized securities platform\n- Solana's tokenized stock holders reached 200,000 users (new all-time high)\n- SEC approved Paxos as the first blockchain-based clearing agency in the US\n- Ondo Finance founder Nathan Allman's unexpected death significantly impacted the RWA sector\n\n## US Regulation Developments\n- Bitcoin perpetual futures approved in the United States for the first time\n- \"CLARITY Act\" advancing to strengthen crypto regulatory framework\n- Crypto spending in 2026 elections exceeded $500 million\n- Conflict emerged between Ripple and Senator Elizabeth Warren regarding OCC Trust Charters\n\n## Network Upgrades\n- Sui experienced multiple major outages within 24 hours\n- Sei announced Giga upgrade roadmap targeting 200,000 TPS and 400ms finality throughout 2026\n- Base launched Azul Upgrade on mainnet\n- Bittensor activated Dynamic TAO on May 25, restructuring network economics with 67 competing subnets\n\n## Institutional Adoption Signals\nForeign US Treasury holdings dropped to $2.68 trillion (lowest since 2012), indicating weakening international demand. The equity risk premium nearly disappeared, reaching lowest levels since 2000."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"540a8677-8f36-4c07-82da-2bc4457d53ef","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:03:08.192Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Crypto & alternative research"}
