{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TKH26U6CWQ8B4QrEcCWsCA","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"CME FedWatch year-end 2026 rate cuts priced June July September FOMC late May 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"FedWatch - CME Group\",\"url\":\"https://www.cmegroup.com/markets/interest-rates/cme-fedwatch-tool.html\"},{\"title\":\"US Fed Funds Interest Rate: Latest Updates and Trends\",\"url\":\"https://growbeansprout.com/tools/fedwatch\"},{\"title\":\"Trading Fed Rate Probabilities: How to Use the CME FedWatch Tool to Gauge Market Sentiment - Switch Markets\",\"url\":\"https://www.switchmarkets.com/learn/how-to-use-cme-fedwatch-tool\"},{\"title\":\"Fed Rate Monitor Tool - Investing.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.investing.com/central-banks/fed-rate-monitor\"},{\"title\":\"CME FedWatch Tool User Guide – CME Group - CME Group\",\"url\":\"https://www.cmegroup.com/tools-information/quikstrike/cme-fedwatch-tool-user-guide.html\"},{\"title\":\"Fed Rate Forecast 2026: How Many Cuts? When Will Rates Go Down? │ PrimeRates\",\"url\":\"https://primerates.com/primerate/fed-rate-forecast-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Fed Rate Change Probability 2026 | FOMC Meeting Odds & Interest Rate Forecast\",\"url\":\"https://centralbank.watch/federal-reserve/\"},{\"title\":\"US - FedWatch Rate Forecast (2026) | MacroMicro\",\"url\":\"https://en.macromicro.me/charts/144242/us-number-yearend-rate-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Fed rate cut by...? Predictions & Odds 2026 | Polymarket\",\"url\":\"https://polymarket.com/event/fed-rate-cut-by-629\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what the CME FedWatch data shows as of late May 2026:\n\n## June 2026 FOMC Meeting (June 16-17)\nCME FedWatch currently shows roughly a 28% probability of a 25bp cut at the June meeting and a 70% probability the Fed holds again.\n\n## July 2026 FOMC Meeting\nMarkets are pricing in a high probability of rates remaining unchanged at the July FOMC meeting, reflecting expectations of a \"wait and see\" approach as policymakers assess economic data.\n\n## September 2026 FOMC Meeting\nThe search results don't provide specific probability data for the September meeting, but they indicate that market expectations currently point to potential further rate cuts in the second half of 2026, with June being the earliest likely date.\n\n## Year-End 2026 Outlook\nOverall, market-implied pricing from fed funds futures reflects trader consensus favoring no cuts or only delayed action through year-end. Recent data is dominating market positioning: April CPI, released May 12, ran hot at 3.8% headline — its highest annual reading since 2023, driven largely by energy prices — while the May 8 jobs report showed the labor market still on solid footing with payrolls expanding modestly.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"81add6a1-2b25-4e61-be35-7492f0851064","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:03:55.638Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KqNmv8obzW5Lfcu1QgBDtq","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"FOMC minutes April 2026 meeting released May 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"The Fed - April 28-29, 2026 FOMC Meeting\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/fomcpresconf20260429.htm\"},{\"title\":\"The Fed - Meeting calendars and information\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/fomccalendars.htm\"},{\"title\":\"FOMC meeting minutes released for April 2026 record\",\"url\":\"https://en.cryptonomist.ch/2026/05/20/fomc-meeting-minutes-april-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"FOMC Minutes, April 28-29, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/fomcminutes20260429.htm\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - Minutes of the Federal Open Market Committee, April 28-29, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/pressreleases/monetary20260520a.htm\"},{\"title\":\"FOMC minutes today, April PCE ahead: a critical two-week calendar - Kraken Blog Kraken Blog\",\"url\":\"https://blog.kraken.com/economic-brief/may-20-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve on X: \\\"We have posted the minutes from the #FOMC meeting held April 28-29, 2026: https://t.co/eFNah62zbz\\\" / X\",\"url\":\"https://x.com/federalreserve/status/2057159951852671180\"},{\"title\":\"Fed Meeting Minutes Preview: What Signals to Watch For?\",\"url\":\"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/economic/central-banks/261915387-fed-fomc-kevin-warsh-inflation-cpi-interest-rate-policy-tradingkey\"},{\"title\":\"Fed officials see rate hike ahead if inflation stays elevated, minutes show\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/20/fed-officials-see-rate-hike-ahead-if-inflation-stays-elevated-minutes-show.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I have found comprehensive information about the FOMC minutes from the April 2026 meeting that were released in May 2026.\n\n## Release Information\n\nThe Federal Reserve released the minutes of the Federal Open Market Committee meeting held on April 28-29, 2026, with the release date on May 20, 2026. The minutes for each regularly scheduled meeting of the Committee are generally published three weeks after the day of the policy decision.\n\n## Key Meeting Details\n\nThe committee voted to hold the federal funds target range at 3.50%–3.75%, noting that inflation remains elevated, in part reflecting rising global energy prices and that Middle East developments are contributing to uncertainty about the economic outlook.\n\nThe meeting featured four \"no\" votes, the most since 1992, and an apparently heightened level of disagreement about where policy should go. A majority of Federal Reserve officials anticipated that interest rate increases would be necessary if the Iran war continued to aggravate inflation.\n\n## Significance\n\nKevin Warsh was confirmed as Fed chair on May 13 in a 54–45 Senate vote; his first FOMC meeting is June 16–17. The April minutes represent the last complete record of committee deliberations under the previous leadership structure.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"13ad3e60-f160-4080-b071-ac433396009f","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:03:55.974Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013esFLSpfSjsqpaceHWwHep","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Treasury yields Friday May 29 2026 close 10-year 2-year weekly recap fixed income\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"10-Year Treasury Constant Maturity Minus 2-Year Treasury Constant Maturity (T10Y2Y) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/T10Y2Y\"},{\"title\":\"Market Yield on U.S. Treasury Securities at 10-Year Constant Maturity, Quoted on an Investment Basis (DGS10) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/DGS10\"},{\"title\":\"Treasury Yields Snapshot: May 29, 2026 - dshort - Advisor Perspectives\",\"url\":\"https://www.advisorperspectives.com/dshort/updates/2026/05/29/treasury-yields-snapshot-may-29-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Market Yield on U.S. Treasury Securities at 2-Year Constant Maturity, Quoted on an Investment Basis (DGS2) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/DGS2\"},{\"title\":\"US 10 Year Treasury Note Yield - Quote - Chart - Historical Data - News\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/united-states/government-bond-yield\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Reserve Board - H.15 - Selected Interest Rates (Daily) - May 29, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalreserve.gov/releases/h15/\"},{\"title\":\"U.S. Treasury Yield Curve\",\"url\":\"https://streetstats.finance/rates/treasuries\"},{\"title\":\"US10Y: U.S. 10 Year Treasury - Stock Price, Quote and News - CNBC\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/quotes/US10Y\"},{\"title\":\"Market Yield on U.S. Treasury Securities at 30-Year Constant Maturity, Quoted on an Investment Basis (DGS30) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/DGS30\"},{\"title\":\"Daily Treasury Rates | U.S. Department of the Treasury\",\"url\":\"https://home.treasury.gov/resource-center/data-chart-center/interest-rates/TextView?type=daily_treasury_bill_rates&field_tdr_date_value=2026\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a summary of Treasury yields for Friday, May 29, 2026:\n\n## Friday Close (May 29, 2026)\n\nThe 10-year note finished at 4.45% while the 2-year note ended at 3.98%. The 10-year to 2-year spread was 0.47%.\n\n## Weekly Context\n\nThe yield on the 10-year US Treasury note eased to around 4.44% on Friday, touching its lowest level in more than two weeks as reports of a tentative peace agreement between the US and Iran helped ease market concerns. \n\nThe yield on the 10-year US Treasury note fell to 4.46%, extending the drop from the 16-month high of 4.7% touched on May 20th as reports of an interim deal between the US and Iran limited the inflationary outlook.\n\n## Fixed Income Drivers\n\nData released on Thursday showed that both headline and core PCE monthly inflation came in below expectations although annual readings remained well above the Fed's target at 3.8% and 3.3%. Markets continue to expect the Federal Reserve to keep interest rates unchanged well into next year.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"add6646a-80f9-44aa-b290-ed7dc53454f7","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:03:56.021Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
