{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_016HxyK3d5EUdm4BKmEp8kt8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TeajSn6Gfk36Lph3Ce12TP","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bigpic/projects/bigpic-markets/eagle-eye/W22_2026-05-31/04_crypto_alternative.md","content":"# Crypto & Alternative — Eagle Eye W22\n\n*Point-in-time snapshot as of Sunday, 2026-05-31 (Pacific). Window: trading week ending Fri 2026-05-29 + breaking news through now. Crypto trades 24/7 — current weekend prices labeled below.*\n\n**One-line takeaway:** Risk-off week. US airstrikes on Iran near the Strait of Hormuz triggered ~$1B in liquidations and pushed BTC below $73K; spot Bitcoin ETFs bled ~$1.4B over a 10-session outflow streak (longest since 2024). BTC sits ~$73.8K this weekend on Iran-truce hopes, ETH languishes near the $2,000 line, and BTC dominance has climbed toward ~60% as alts underperform.\n\n---\n\n## Bitcoin\n\n**Current price (as of Sun 2026-05-31):** ~**$73,800–$73,900** (BTC traded $73,856, +~0.5% on the day per market data on 5/31; Coinbase quoted $73,876 on 5/30–5/31). This is a modest stabilization after a sharp mid-week drop.\n\n**Friday 2026-05-29 close/level:** ~**$73,100–$73,640**. Fortune logged $73,105.71 at 9:15am ET Friday; Phemex showed BTC/USDT at $73,642.90 by Friday with a 24h range of $72,561–$73,922. Both BTC and ETH \"opened at their lowest levels all week\" on Friday.\n\n**Weekly action:** Net **down** on the week and locked in a tightening compression range below all major moving averages. BTC dropped below **$73,000** on 2026-05-28 after US airstrikes on Iran near the Strait of Hormuz (plus fresh sanctions) sparked a broad risk-asset sell-off and ~$1B in crypto liquidations. It briefly bounced back near **$74,000** on 5/29 on reports of a 60-day Iran truce extension on Trump's desk, then drifted to ~$72,500 intra-week before stabilizing. Monthly: down ~4.4% from ~$76,500 a month ago. BTC is ~30% below its 2025-10-06 all-time high of $126,198.\n\n**Key levels:**\n- Resistance: ~$75,500 (7-day MA), then the $77,000–$79,500 psychological zone that has repeatedly capped rallies.\n- Support: $72,500 (recent intra-week low); deeper support cited at $62,872 (52-week close low).\n- Momentum is oversold (MFI ~28, lowest in ~4 months).\n\n**BTC dominance:** Elevated and rising — most trackers put **BTC.D in the high-50s to ~60%** (TradingView Hub cited 57.3% mid-month; other data showed dominance edging to ~60.2% by week-end). Rising dominance reflects capital rotating out of altcoins into BTC. BTC market cap ~$1.33T.\n\n---\n\n## Ethereum\n\n**Current price (as of Sun 2026-05-31):** ~**$2,000–$2,025** (CoinMarketCap-style quote $2,025.49 on 5/30; recap data pegged ETH \"near $2,000\" into the weekend). ETH is hovering on its psychological support line.\n\n**Friday 2026-05-29 / weekly action:** ETH fell **below the $2,000 psychological support on 2026-05-28** and entered a bearish range, finishing the week roughly flat-to-down near $2,000–$2,069. The 14-day RSI sat ~31–33 (oversold). Analyst Ali Martinez flagged a path to **$1,560** on a weekly close below $1,850. ETH market cap ~$233B.\n\n**Key levels:**\n- Near-term consolidation band: ~$1,975–$2,135.\n- Bearish trigger: weekly close below $1,850 → $1,560 risk.\n- Overhead: 50-day MA ~$2,194, 200-day MA ~$2,510.\n\n**ETH/BTC ratio:** ~**0.0272 BTC** (range over the prior 7 days: 0.02721–0.02758). ETH continues to underperform BTC — the ratio is grinding lower, consistent with the dominance rotation toward Bitcoin.\n\n---\n\n## Altcoins & DeFi\n\n**Major coins (week ending 5/29 / current weekend levels):**\n- **SOL (Solana):** ~**$81–$83**. Bearish on the weekly timeframe; dropped ~5% in the mid-week liquidation cascade. Bright spot: Solana tokenized-stock holders hit a new ATH of ~200,000 users.\n- **XRP:** ~**$1.27–$1.34** (fell to $1.27 Thursday, recovered to ~$1.33–$1.34 by 5/31). Relative outperformer: order books showed ~7x more bid than sell orders, and XRP ETFs took in ~$35M (5/20–5/29) even as BTC/ETH funds shed ~$2B. Still neutral-to-bearish unless it reclaims the $1.41–$1.48 EMA cluster. Support $1.27 (loss → $1.11); resistance $1.61 → $2.\n- **AVAX (Avalanche):** ~**$8.90–$9.02**. Bearish weekly structure.\n- **LINK (Chainlink):** ~**$8.89** (5/29).\n- **Notable mover — XLM (Stellar):** surged **~33–50% on the week** after DTCC announced plans to integrate with its tokenized-securities platform — the standout altcoin move of the week (RWA/tokenization narrative).\n\n**Liquidations:** A long-skewed market got hit hard. ~**$1B in total liquidations** mid-week tied to the Iran shock; a separate 24h window saw **$333M** wiped (≈85% longs; BTC ~$116M, ETH ~$53M). HYPE (Hyperliquid) -3% on 5/27.\n\n**DeFi TVL / RWA:** Sentiment dented by **near-daily DeFi exploits in 2026** (>$400M–$1B+ lost YTD; April was the worst month for DeFi hacks in 4 years), which CertiK and others cite as the top blocker for institutional/TradFi on-chain adoption. RWA/tokenization remains the strongest structural growth narrative (DTCC/Stellar, Solana tokenized stocks, SEC's Paxos clearing-agency approval). Note: Ondo Finance founder Nathan Allman's unexpected death weighed on RWA sentiment.\n\n**Stablecoins:** Total stablecoin market cap hit a **record ~$321–$322.5B** in late May 2026 (ATH ~$321B in April, ~$322.5B by 5/26). **USDT** ~$189.6B–$190B (new ATH, ~59.2% share, reclaiming share for the first time in 4 months); **USDC** ~$76.4–$77.6B. Ethereum hosts ~55% (~$190B) of stablecoin value. Stablecoins were ~75% of Q1 2026 crypto trading volume. Growth here is the clearest \"risk-on plumbing\" tailwind even amid the price weakness.\n\n---\n\n## ETF Flows\n\n**Spot Bitcoin ETFs — heavy, sustained outflows (the dominant flow story of the week):**\n- **~$1.42B net outflows since 2026-05-25**, marking **10 consecutive sessions of outflows — the first such streak since 2024**. (One framing cited ~$1.55B over six days.)\n- **Wed 2026-05-27** was the worst day: the 11 US spot BTC ETFs lost a combined **$733.4M**, with **BlackRock IBIT -$527.8M** (its second-largest single-day outflow on record / largest since launch by some accounts). Fidelity **FBTC -$60.3M** that day.\n- **Thu 5/28:** -$223.3M (largest one-day bleed in 3+ weeks at the time). **Fri 5/29:** IBIT -$68.9M (or -$177.9M by another count), FBTC -$36.3M; Morgan Stanley's BTC ETF turned negative (-$5.26M).\n- 2026 YTD net inflows have shrunk to roughly **$536M**; total BTC ETF AUM ~$106B.\n\n**Spot Ethereum ETFs:** Also in an outflow stretch in May (e.g., -$104M on 5/7 with ETHA -$26.3M; -$28.1M on 5/20, 8th straight day of withdrawals, ETHA -$30.9M). Despite the May choppiness, BlackRock's **ETHA still held ~$11.67B cumulative net inflows** as of 5/20. Combined BTC+ETH funds shed **~$2B from 5/20–5/29**.\n\n**XRP ETFs:** A rare bright spot — **+~$35M inflows (5/20–5/29)** while BTC/ETH funds bled. Broader digital-asset investment products saw ~$1.47B of outflows the prior week (2nd straight weekly outflow, 3rd-largest single-week withdrawal of 2026).\n\n---\n\n## Regulation & Institutional\n\n- **GENIUS Act implementation (stablecoins):** Treasury launched its first GENIUS Act rulemaking (87-page proposal); additional issuer rules (licensing, capital, custody, AML) are due **2026-07-18**. The framework (100% liquid reserves, monthly disclosures) is credited with re-pricing Bitcoin's \"monetary premium\" (CoinDesk, 5/27/2026).\n- **CLARITY Act** advancing — would classify Bitcoin as a commodity, removing the regulatory limbo that currently complicates pension/endowment allocation and index inclusion.\n- **Bitcoin perpetual futures approved in the US for the first time** (per weekly recap, week of 5/30) — a notable market-structure milestone.\n- **SEC approved Paxos as the first blockchain-based clearing agency** in the US — a structural win for tokenized settlement.\n- **DTCC** announced plans to integrate Stellar (XLM) with its tokenized-securities platform (drove the XLM rally).\n- **Institutional positioning (Q1 2026 13Fs):** **Goldman Sachs fully liquidated its XRP and Solana ETF positions** while keeping its Bitcoin ETF allocation largely intact (~$700M) — a \"flight to BTC quality\" within crypto.\n- **Sanctions/enforcement:** The US Treasury seized nearly **$1B in Iran-linked crypto assets** amid the conflict.\n- Friction: Ripple vs. Sen. Elizabeth Warren over OCC Trust Charters; crypto 2026 election spending topped $500M.\n\n---\n\n## Weekend Developments (if any)\n\n- **US–Iran conflict drove the tape (5/28–5/31):** US airstrikes near the Strait of Hormuz + new sanctions on 2026-05-28 sent BTC below $73K and triggered ~$1B in liquidations. By 5/29, reports of a **60-day truce extension** awaiting Trump's signature (and talk of the Strait reopening) sparked a partial relief bounce toward $74K. Heading into the weekend the market stayed cautious — risk of re-escalation vs. truce hopes — with BTC stabilizing ~$73.8K. (Strait carries ~20% of global petroleum; a reopening would ease the oil/inflation premium on risk assets.)\n- **Macro backdrop:** US equities ironically hit ATHs on de-escalation hopes; but the **30-yr Treasury yield hit ~5.19% (highest since 2007)** and the 10-yr ~4.6%, raising the opportunity cost of non-yielding BTC. Markets await Core CPI/PCE for Fed rate-cut signals.\n- **Stablecoin hack — StablR (weekend of 5/24–5/26):** European issuer StablR's 1-of-3 minting multisig was compromised; attacker minted ~8.35M USDR + 4.5M EURR (~$13.5M unbacked) and netted ~$2.8M. Root cause was key-management failure, not smart-contract code. A reminder that \"digital dollars\" can still break — though contained and not a major-stablecoin de-peg.\n- **Network reliability:** Sui suffered multiple outages within 24 hours; Base shipped its Azul mainnet upgrade; Sei announced a \"Giga\" roadmap (200k TPS target); Bittensor activated Dynamic TAO (5/25).\n- **No major BTC/ETH or large-cap stablecoin de-peg over the weekend** beyond the contained StablR incident as of this snapshot.\n\n---\n\n## Sources\n\n- [Fortune — Current price of Bitcoin for May 29, 2026](https://fortune.com/article/price-of-bitcoin-05-29-2026/) — 2026-05-29\n- [Phemex — BTC Price Today May 29, 2026: Bitcoin ETF Outflows](https://phemex.com/blogs/btc-price-today-may-29-2026-bitcoin-etf-outflows) — 2026-05-29\n- [Coinbase — Bitcoin (BTC) Price](https://www.coinbase.com/price/bitcoin) — accessed 2026-05-31\n- [cryptonews.net — AI model sets Bitcoin price target for May 31, 2026](https://cryptonews.net/news/bitcoin/32794481/) — 2026-05-31\n- [Yahoo Finance — Bitcoin and ethereum prices today, Friday, May 29, 2026 (US-Iran truce)](https://finance.yahoo.com/personal-finance/investing/article/bitcoin-and-ethereum-prices-today-friday-may-29-2026-prices-open-lower-despite-news-of-us-iran-truce-115046286.html) — 2026-05-29\n- [CoinDesk — Bitcoin drops below $73,000 as U.S. strikes on Iran spark $1 billion liquidations](https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/05/28/bitcoin-drops-below-usd73-000-as-us-strikes-on-iran-spark-usd1-billion-liquidations) — 2026-05-28\n- [Investing.com — Bitcoin rises near $74k after 7-wk low on Iran truce extension hopes](https://www.investing.com/news/cryptocurrency-news/bitcoin-rises-near-74k-after-7wk-low-on-iran-truce-extension-hopes-4715939) — 2026-05-29\n- [CoinGape — Crypto Market Weekly: Bitcoin ETF Outflows Persist, Ethereum Enters Bearish Range, XRP Spot Bids Surge](https://coingape.com/markets/crypto-market-weekly-bitcoin-etf-outflows-persist-ethereum-enters-bearish-range-and-xrp-spot-bids-surge/) — 2026-05-30\n- [CryptoTicker — Crypto Prices Today: Bitcoin Holds $73K Amid Institutional De-Risking](https://cryptoticker.io/en/crypto-prices-today-bitcoin-ethereum-solana-macro-forecast/) — 2026-05-30\n- [Millionero — Weekly Crypto Recap: Bitcoin Falls on Iran Tensions, Tokenized Assets, US Regulation, Network Upgrades](https://blog.millionero.com/blog/weekly-crypto-recap-bitcoin-falls-on-iran-tensions-as-tokenized-assets-us-regulation-and-network-upgrades-take-center-stage/) — 2026-05-30\n- [Blockhead — Bitcoin ETFs Post Ninth Straight Day of Outflows as IBIT Notches Near-Record Redemption](https://www.blockhead.co/2026/05/29/bitcoin-etfs-post-ninth-straight-day-of-outflows-as-ibit-notches-near-record-redemption/) — 2026-05-29\n- [BitcoinFoundation — Bitcoin ETF Flows May 2026: 6-Day Outflow Streak](https://bitcoinfoundation.org/news/crypto-etfs-news/crypto-etf-may/) — May 2026\n- [CryptoTimes — Crypto Market Today: BTC, ETH, XRP Slip as $333M Liquidations Hit Longs](https://www.cryptotimes.io/2026/05/27/crypto-market-today-btc-eth-xrp-slip-as-333m-liquidations-hit-longs/) — 2026-05-27\n- [Statista — Ethereum price history May 27, 2026](https://www.statista.com/statistics/806453/price-of-ethereum/) — 2026-05-27\n- [MetaMask — Solana Price](https://metamask.io/price/solana) — accessed 2026-05-31\n- [MetaMask — Avalanche Price](https://metamask.io/price/avalanche) — accessed 2026-05-31\n- [CoinMarketCap — Latest XRP News & Updates](https://coinmarketcap.com/cmc-ai/xrp/latest-updates/) — accessed 2026-05-31\n- [KuCoin — Stablecoin Liquidity Hits $320.6B Milestone in May 2026](https://www.kucoin.com/blog/Stablecoin-Liquidity-Hits-$320B-Milestone-in-May-2026) — May 2026\n- [Cryptonomist — Stablecoin market capitalization hits $322.5B record](https://en.cryptonomist.ch/2026/05/26/stablecoin-market-capitalization-322-5b-record/) — 2026-05-26\n- [CoinDesk Research — Stablecoins and Tokenized Asset Report (April 2026)](https://www.coindesk.com/research/stablecoins-and-tokenized-asset-report-april-2026) — April 2026\n- [KuCoin — Ethereum spot ETFs $104M net outflow on May 7, 2026](https://www.kucoin.com/news/flash/ethereum-spot-etfs-recorded-104m-net-outflow-on-may-7-2026) — 2026-05-07\n- [KuCoin — Ethereum Spot ETFs $28.14M Net Outflow on May 20, 2026](https://www.kucoin.com/news/flash/ethereum-spot-etfs-record-28-14m-net-outflow-on-may-20-2026) — 2026-05-20\n- [CoinDesk — How the GENIUS Act repriced bitcoin's monetary premium](https://www.coindesk.com/coindesk-indices/2026/05/27/crypto-long-and-short-how-the-genius-act-repriced-bitcoin-s-monetary-premium) — 2026-05-27\n- [Bitcoin Magazine — U.S. Treasury Launches First GENIUS Act Rulemaking With 87-Page Proposal](https://bitcoinmagazine.com/news/u-s-treasury-launches-genius-act-proposal) — 2026\n- [Crypto Briefing — Goldman Sachs dumps XRP and Solana ETFs, doubles down on Bitcoin](https://cryptobriefing.com/goldman-sachs-dumps-xrp-solana-etfs-bitcoin/) — 2026\n- [Gizmodo — The Latest Stablecoin Hack (StablR)](https://gizmodo.com/the-latest-stablecoin-hack-is-a-reminder-that-digital-dollars-can-still-break-2000763481) — 2026-05\n- [CoinDesk — DeFi vulnerabilities are TradFi's biggest blocker as protocols hit by near-daily exploits (CertiK)](https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/05/28/defi-vulnerabilities-are-tradfi-biggest-blocker-as-protocols-hit-by-near-daily-exploits-certik) — 2026-05-28\n- [TradingView Hub — Bitcoin Dominance May 2026 (BTC.D 57.3%)](https://www.tv-hub.org/guide/bitcoin-dominance) — May 2026\n\n*Note: Sub-daily crypto prices move continuously; figures labeled \"current\" reflect the latest available quotes around 2026-05-30/31 and may differ slightly from live prices at read time. Where window-specific data was unavailable, levels were drawn from the nearest in-window source and labeled accordingly.*\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2477,"cache_read_input_tokens":79079,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2477,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PHSkBGNFVsYNfGY6YDTHaK","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de1