{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MgHaiziiBLKfd6fNAzZcMu","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"sovereign credit rating action US Treasury Moody's S&P Fitch May 2026 downgrade outlook\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"List of countries by credit rating - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_by_credit_rating\"},{\"title\":\"Rating: United States Credit Rating 2026 | countryeconomy.com\",\"url\":\"https://countryeconomy.com/ratings/usa\"},{\"title\":\"United States federal government credit-rating downgrades - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_federal_government_credit-rating_downgrades\"},{\"title\":\"Moody's 2026 Investment Grade Ratings\",\"url\":\"https://investmentgrade.com/moodys-investment-grade-ratings/\"},{\"title\":\"Moody's Downgrade of the U.S. Credit Rating | BNY Investments\",\"url\":\"https://www.bny.com/investments/us/en/intermediary/articles/markets-and-economy/moodys-downgrade-of-the-us-credit-rating.html\"},{\"title\":\"United States - Credit Rating\",\"url\":\"https://tradingeconomics.com/united-states/rating\"},{\"title\":\"Global sovereign and emerging markets outlooks 2026 executive summary\",\"url\":\"https://www.moodys.com/web/en/us/insights/credit-risk/outlooks/global-sovereigns-2026.html\"},{\"title\":\"USA Sovereign credit ratings - data, chart | TheGlobalEconomy.com\",\"url\":\"https://www.theglobaleconomy.com/USA/credit_rating/\"},{\"title\":\"Moody's Ratings downgrades United States ...\",\"url\":\"https://ratings.moodys.com/ratings-news/443154\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what has occurred regarding U.S. sovereign credit ratings:\n\n## Recent Rating Actions\n\nOn May 16, 2025, Moody's downgraded the US debt rating to Aa1 from Aaa. Moody's cited rising federal debt ratios and interest payment costs projected to reach levels significantly higher than similarly rated sovereigns.\n\nOn August 1, 2023 Fitch downgraded the United States's long-term credit rating from AAA to AA+. S&P had downgraded earlier in 2011.\n\n## Current Ratings (as of May 2026)\n\nAs of the most recent data available:\n- Standard & Poor's credit rating for the United States stands at AA+ with stable outlook.\n- Moody's credit rating for the United States was last set at Aa1 with stable outlook.\n\n## Significance\n\nIn May 2025, Moody's downgraded the United States sovereign rating from Aaa to Aa1, ending a rating continuity that dated to 1917 and bringing the last major agency into line with S&P and Fitch, both of which had already moved the U.S. below the top tier.\n\nAs of May 2026, there have been no additional downgrade actions announced by the major rating agencies in May 2026, and all three major agencies (Moody's, S&P, and Fitch) maintain stable outlooks on their U.S. ratings.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"53a66413-9f6e-41d0-af32-ad86754cc654","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:04:30.847Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GyMYT2D5xeN9PqdBKtSrCH","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"corporate bond credit spreads tighten widen May 2026 high yield issuance weekly\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"ICE BofA US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLH0A0HYM2) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLH0A0HYM2\"},{\"title\":\"Corporate Bonds - Investment Grade & High Yield Bond Interest Rates | StreetStats\",\"url\":\"https://streetstats.finance/rates/corporates\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Corporate Credit Outlook | Charles Schwab\",\"url\":\"https://www.schwab.com/learn/story/corporate-bond-outlook\"},{\"title\":\"What Might 2026 Hold for U.S. Corporate Bonds?\",\"url\":\"https://www.americancentury.com/insights/corporate-bond-outlook/\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA BB US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLH0A1HYBB) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLH0A1HYBB\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Investment Grade Bond Statistics: IG OAS 77 bps, Yield ...\",\"url\":\"https://investmentgrade.com/investment-grade-bond-statistics-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"US - Credit Spread | Spread | Collection | MacroMicro\",\"url\":\"https://en.macromicro.me/collections/384/spreads/930/us-credit-spread\"},{\"title\":\"ICE BofA CCC & Lower US High Yield Index Option-Adjusted Spread (BAMLH0A3HYC) | FRED | St. Louis Fed\",\"url\":\"https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/BAMLH0A3HYC\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what I found regarding corporate bond credit spreads and high yield issuance in May 2026:\n\n## Credit Spread Movements\n\nThe first five months of 2026 produced a sustained tightening of credit spreads, an expansion of new issue activity, and a continuation of the multi-year \"up in quality\" theme that has characterized institutional fixed-income allocation since the post-pandemic rate cycle began. More specifically, option-adjusted spreads on the broad ICE BofA U.S. Corporate Index compressed from approximately 95 basis points at year-end 2025 to 77 basis points by mid-May 2026.\n\nThe U.S. investment grade corporate bond market entered the second quarter of 2026 with option-adjusted spreads at 77 basis points over Treasuries, a level not seen on a sustained basis since the pre-financial-crisis era.\n\n## Investment Grade Issuance\n\nInvestment grade corporate issuance reached approximately $620 billion in Q1 2026 alone, contributing to the largest quarterly U.S. corporate bond issuance total since Q2 2020.\n\n## High Yield Outlook\n\nRegarding high yield bonds, low credit spreads are a key reason behind a cautious view of high-yield bonds, with the average option-adjusted spread of the Bloomberg US Corporate High-Yield Bond Index closing November at just 2.7%, well below its 20-year average of 4.9%.\n\nThe search results indicate that May 2026 saw continued **tightening** of credit spreads rather than widening, with spreads compressing to historically tight levels.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPmvo8LP7wReL3gw7pS53N","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"29eb320b-f460-4889-b44d-4e7334a54b82","timestamp":"2026-05-31T23:04:30.983Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Rates, credit & Fed research"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SmKvLwJhpXd1FUZ8eFid4y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Report written to `/home/bigpic/projects/bigpic-markets/eagle-eye/W22_2026-05-31/03_commodities_forex.md`.\n\nThe week was dominated by the ~3-month-old US–Israel–Iran war and the closed Strait of Hormuz: oil cratered as markets priced in a tentative 60-day US–Iran ceasefire/Hormuz-reopening deal, with WTI closing ~$87.36 (-1.73% Fri) and Brent down ~17-19% on the month — its worst since the 2020 Covid crash and now ~20% off 2026 peaks. The structural shock was the UAE's formal exit from OPEC/OPEC+ (effective May 1), leaving it free to ramp output once Hormuz reopens and raising price-war risk. The biggest weekend development: Trump declined to sign the deal, twice sending the text back with hardened demands (Fri 5/29 and again per 5/31 reporting) while Hegseth warned the US is ready to resume Gulf combat — leaving oil with sharp two-sided risk into Monday. Elsewhere: gold bounced hard Friday to ~$4,541 (still -0.8% on the month after fading as a safe haven), silver outperformed at ~$76, copper held ~$6.40 on AI-demand strength, lithium hit a ~3-year high (bullish for the energy-storage/critical-minerals theses), and DXY sat near 99 (flat week, +1% month) with EUR/USD ~1.166 and USD/JPY ~159.3. File confirmed written."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8326,"cache_read_input_tokens":81739,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8326,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q8Kwt517HqYVMRhJgQ1kZ1","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"958b056b-83e6-4d6a-8411-1b80f3b40218","request_id":"req_011CbbUxrTNKM9PSVzaybNGe","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_de