{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01QNti94zg65yLbUehRJLLQn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Report written to `/home/bigpic/projects/bigpic-markets/eagle-eye/W22_2026-05-31/01_equities_sectors.md`.\n\nThe biggest equity stories of the week: US stocks closed May at record highs with the S&P 500 (7,580), Nasdaq (26,973), and Dow (first close above 51,000) all setting records — the S&P's ninth straight weekly gain, the longest streak since 2023 — led by a tech/AI rally and a ~19% May collapse in oil on a US-Iran 60-day ceasefire MOU. Dell stole the show with its best day ever (~33% pop on $16.1B AI server revenue, +757% YoY, and a sharply raised FY27 guide), while Snowflake's beat sparked a software rally and Zscaler's soft guidance crushed it ~30% (briefly dragging PANW/CRWD). The standout weekend developments are AI/space IPO momentum — SpaceX expected to debut within ~2 weeks (S-1 filed), OpenAI working on a confidential filing, and Anthropic's ~$965B (near-$1T) raise — plus a quantum-stock rip earlier in the week on a planned ~$2B US government quantum funding/equity-stake program. Breadth is constructive but uneven (~59% of S&P names above their 200-DMA, RSI ~73.6 overbought, VIX 15.32), and Sunday-night futures are flat heading into a payrolls week. File confirmed written."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8824,"cache_read_input_tokens":153260,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8824,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018dZEMFFbxCBMwW5jUrv2aX","session_id":"fe1a4df5-a4ab-4fab-90bd-ba1de175a1ca","uuid":"ae788631-79ec-478f-b78f-1bc2c7383bce","request_id":"req_011CbbV1DTEPZnEJZG9H8mGR","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Equities & sectors r